title: Feature (RW-Valet Annual): Update folder status with renewal (Ready for PROD Deployment)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 2-Should Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA
body:
Acceptance Criteria (Permit Renewal)

The following steps were performed in RW-Valet Parking Annual Folder for Renewal
-- A bill was created for fees to be paid
-- The fees in the folder were paid (through portal or Back Office)
-- In the Annual Valet Permitting Process, Process info fields were updated with new Issue date and new Expiry Date
-- Attempt 'Update issue and expiry dates' was made in the annual valet permitting process, along with attempt comments.

Expected result: Folder should update folder status from 'Expired' to 'Active', and also update issue and expiry dates based on process info.

Actual result: Folder updated issue and expiry dates, but did not update folder status to 'Active'

title: TDS: Add to completeness check on SP folder
labels: Type: Feature, Impact: 2-Major, Need: 1-Must Have, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA
body:
### As a TDS project manager, I need to be included on the completeness check process for the SP folder. 

**Stakeholder:** Sangeeta, Amber

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Applies to the SP folder
- When attempt 'Distribute CC Reviews' is saved on process 5116 Completeness Check Distribution: 
    - The system inserts process code 51834 CC ATD Review
    - The process is assigned ATD-Reviewers
    - Process start & end dates to mirror the other CC process that are inserted at this time (9 business days)
- When ATD Review process is inserted, the system inserts 'ATD Review' (10091) document on the document tab
    - This document, if generated & sent, merges into 100001 SP - Completeness Check Results Letter
- When 'Incomplete' attempt is saved on 51834 CC ATD Review, the system validates 'ATD Review' (10091) document
    - If document has not been sent, system throws error "Please generate and complete your review document and then return to this process"
- When 'Complete Without Site Visit' attempt is saved on process 5116 Completeness Check Distribution, the system validates 51834 CC ATD Review process status:
    - If status is not 'Complete' or 'No Review Required', the system throws this error: All review processes must be marked Complete or No Review Required to give this attempt
- If 51834 CC ATD Review process status is 'Incomplete' when the attempt result 'Entered' is saved on process 51118 Completeness Check Update, the system will insert 51834 CC ATD Review process. 
    - Assign process to ATD-Reviewers
    - Process start & end dates to mirror the other CC process that are inserted at this time (7 calendar days)

**Notes:**
- This feature is programmed on the C8 folder and can be referenced as needed. 

**Business Justification:**
We have to rely on DSD Intake staff to manually assign the CC reviews to ATD.  It takes a lot of time on our part to manually search for pending CC cases, then create a process and document for each one, with no guarantee that it will be rejected in time.  When the CC projects don't get assigned to us in time, we miss the review deadline.  The project is deemed complete after 10 days; and it may have a TIA associated with it.  We end up missing SP applications resulting in loss of review causing transportation challenges in the City.  Also, we will get our review fees missed and/ or not added in a timely manner.

title: FY22 Backlog: Add TCP Review Fee to SP, GP
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Project: FY22 AMANDA Fee Updates
body:
ROW will be charging for In-Process TCP Review fees beginning Oct. 1, 2021. This will require updates to the SP & GP folders (both owned by DSD).

**Stakeholders:**
- (ATD) Ryan, Darren, Laura
- (DSD) Deborah F, Zachary W., Roderick B, Zackary M.

### Summary
- **SP:** ATD Staff will identify the TCP Fee requirement during CC, and the fee will be included in the big invoice that intake creates after CC. 
- **GP:** When ATD staff identifies the TCP Fee requirement, they will use a folder process to insert the fee as a stand-alone invoice.

## Acceptance Criteria


### SP folder Acceptance Criteria
**The following process info needs to be configured in the AMANDA Admin Module**
- Info Description: TCP Review Fee Required? 
- Info Type: Boolean
- Info Default Value: Yes
- Info Process: CC Traffic Control Process (51830)

**The following fee logic needs to be added for SP folder fees**
- Process Info field 'TCP Review Fee Required?' needs to be added to CC Traffic Control Process (51830)
- When user makes attempt 'Completed without Site Visit' on Completeness Check Distribution Process (51116) AND Info field 'TCP Review Fee Required?' Process Info in CC Traffic Control Process (51830) is answered 'Yes', System must insert TCP Review Fee and ATD Tech Surcharge Fee (50174).
    - The two fees should insert along with the other fees that are inserted w/ this procedure / They should not be on a stand-alone bill unless no other fees are inserted. 
- The system should not waiver the TCP Review Fee and ATD Tech Surcharge Fee when other SP fees are waived (Fee waiver logic exists in SMART Housing Folder Infos 50920 and 50921).

### GP Folder Acceptance Criteria
**The following Process attempt needs to be added in AMANDA Admin Module**
Attempt Description - Add TCP Fee
Process - Traffic Control Review (51300)

**The following fee logic needs to be added for GP folders**
- Attempt 'Add TCP Fee' needs to be added to Traffic Control Review Process (51300)
- When user makes attempt Add TCP Fee in Traffic Control Review Process, system should insert TCP Review Fee and ATD Tech Surcharge Fee. 
- System should also bill the inserted TCP Review Fee and ATD Tech Surcharge Fee as part of the same bill 
- The Add TCP Fee attempt should not close the Traffic Control Review Process 



----
**Running Task List**
- [x] (Tracy, 6/3/21) Write draft AC; send to stakeholders for review
- [x] (Tracy) Schedule time w/ Zach for GP training
- [x] (Tracy, 6/23) Write possible solutions for GP specifically
- [x] (Tracy, 6/23) Send draft AC for both SP & GP to Ryan & Darren when they're ready

title: Edit language about response time interval for permits submitted at the ABC Portal
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 2-Should Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Product: AMANDA Portal
body:
### Update Portal text (displayed after submittal) about response times for ROW permit applications. 

- **Current Text:** "The application has been submitted for review by permit specialist, customer should receive a response within 1 to 5 business days."

- **Updated Text:** "The application has been submitted for review by a permit analyst.  Customer should receive a response within 5 business days.  Business days exclude weekends and holidays."

_Darren asked for this update to apply to UC submittals also._

----
### Form Submittal: 
<!-- Email -->
<!-- paloma.amayo-ryan@austintexas.gov -->

> What application are you using?

AMANDA

> Describe the problem.

We recently noticed that we an applicant submits their permit request via ABC Portal, one of the notes that displays states: "The application has been submitted for review by permit specialist, customer should receive a response within 1 to 5 business days."

While there are some permits which are reviewed within 1 business day (i.e. emergency and secondary requests), the vast majority are reviewed closer to the 5 business day mark.  We would like to edit this language to more accurately reflect the review timeline.

> Describe the outcome you'd like to see when this feature is implemented.

We would like to see the language changed to: "The application has been submitted for review by a permit analyst.  Customer should receive a response within 5 business days.  Business days exclude weekends and holidays."

> Describe any workarounds you currently have in place or alternative solutions you've considered.

We have no workarounds.  The current text could explain why we have so many ppl reach out to us just a couple days after submittal with complaints about delays.

> Is there anything else we should know?

N/A

> Requested By
Paloma A.

body:
### As a UC folder applicant, I want system generated emails to efficiently provide me with the information I need to know. 

Due to system programming on the process tab, the UC folder sends out 3 almost identical emails to the folder applicant, usually in rapid succession. 

**Stakeholders:** Jacqueline Lozano, isaiah lewallen
**DTS Manager:** Nate

See issue comments for examples of each email that is sent, and the corresponding process that sent the email. 

**Processes that send the emails:**
Application Review (82005), Permit Completeness check (51065), Web Application Acceptance (70000) and Initial Distribution (51070)

**Acceptance Criteria**

- Only one email should be sent to the Applicant, instead of the 2 or 3 being sent (Process to send Email: TBD on Monday 8/3/2020)

- Set one process to be the Email Trigger. Right now they are Web Application Accepted and Permit Completeness Check (Trigger: TBD on Monday 8/3/2020)

- Disable/remove email trigger from other Process

- Update Verbiage on emails (on #3536)

1. Remove Verbiage in all UC emails stating:
"Deliver one (1) half-size paper plan set to Austin Water at 625 E 10th St (Attention: AW-Infrastructure Management AULCC Review) on the Wednesday two weeks prior to your scheduled AULCC meeting and include a screen print displaying your case, tracking or folder number. Bring a plan set to your scheduled AULCC meeting. "  
2. Verbiage to be changed in the Permit Completeness Check email:
**From** "10th Floor Conference Room, One Texas Center, 505 Barton Springs Road"
**To** "Online via Microsoft TEAMS. You will receive an email invitation with the TEAMS link and optional call in number at a later date"
3. Meeting Date and time will remain the same since they never change (Thursdays at 2pm)
4. Choose 1 of these processes to send one email, turn the email feature on the other 2 processes off. 

**Next Steps:**

- Find lookup table with emails
- Fix the verbiage on emails #3536
- Disable current triggers that send the email to users; Possible triggers Web Application Acceptance (70000) and Permit Completeness Check 51065
- Tie in the sending of email to the Initial Distribution (51070) and the Adjust Review Due Dates (61060)
- Make the Initial Distribution (51070) and the Adjust Review Due Dates (61060) processes not assign users automatically

AMANDA

> Describe the problem.

Maybe V7 will fix this?  Capturing it here so we can be on the lookout.

DS permits are reflecting an "Expires" date (Folder Tab) even though the permit has *not* been reviewed or issued.  The date populating in this field is comping from the related Building Permit expiration date.  It should not be doing this.

title: Automate Cost of Services (COS) Monthly Reporting
labels: Workgroup: Finance, Workgroup: ROW, Type: Data, Type: Reports, Product: AMANDA, Project: FY22 AMANDA Fee Updates
body:
Automate cost of service (COS) reporting. Users must be able to download, on demand, two reports:

- a transaction report which can be uploaded into the AIMs system to transfer funds from other departments to ATD. This is the "JVD" report
- a report which itemizes fees that will be charged to each department, and can be provided to each department for review before processing the transactions in AIMS. Let's call this the "Department Report"


### Resources:
- [Miro board](https://miro.com/app/board/o9J_lrnxMhs=/) with basic data flow
- [Google sheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/132IH0tTLHp9KeuWYN9xhTY7cmad6ojam64jzvU5phPE/edit#gid=983197605) with report template and field mappings
- [Github repo](https://github.com/cityofaustin/atd-cost-of-service-reporting)


### Todo:
- [x] Develop AMANDA SQL Queries
- [x] Develop Knack queries
- [x] Create a sample JVD Report **with real data** for staff review
- [x] Create a sample Department Report **with real data** for staff review
- [x] Write ETL scripts
- [x] Set up database pipeline/infrastructure
- [ ] Determine how reports will be delivered. A UI would be nice, but an email may have to suffice in the near term.

title: Project: AMANDA FY22 Fee Updates
labels: Workgroup: Finance, Workgroup: ROW, Type: Feature, Impact: 1-Severe, Service: Product, Need: 1-Must Have, Epic, Type: Enhancement, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Project Index, Product: AMANDA Portal, Project: FY22 AMANDA Fee Updates
body:
Implementation of ATD FY22 fee schedule updates for fees maintained in the [AMANDA system](https://github.com/cityofaustin/atd-data-tech/issues/4790).

## Background
As part of the [city's yearly budgeting process](https://www.speakupaustin.org/budget-2022), department fee schedules are updated with an implementation date of Oct 1. The scope of FY22 ATD-AMANDA fee updates is considerably large, requiring a project based approach. 


## Scope & Deliverables

**In Scope:**
All AMANDA system updates necessary for staff to be able to assess the approved FY22 fee schedule in the AMANDA system.

**Out of Scope:**

- Fees on the fee schedule that are not, or should not be maintained in AMANDA are out of scope. 
- Any non-AMANDA solutions are also out of scope.


## Timebox
All deliverables must ship by Oct 1, 2021. 

**Components:**
1. Scoping: April - May
2. Technical requirements and documentation: June
3. System development: July
4. User acceptance testing: August
5. Training and implementation: September

title: AMANDA - Street Impact Fee for ATD
labels: Workgroup: SDD, Type: Feature, Product: AMANDA, Project: Street Impact Fee Implimentation
body:
<!-- Email -->
<!-- liane.conte@austintexas.gov -->

> Name

Liane Conte

> What application are you using?

Other / Not Sure

> Describe the problem.

AMANDA programming for new Street Impact Fee for ATD. (not sure if this is considered a "new project" or a new feature in AMANDA)

> Describe the solution you have in mind.

We need to define the way AMANDA will be used for the Street Impact Fee. The ideal solution provides consistency in the application of the Street Impact Fee, accurate and timely information for applicants and reviewers, and is able to be reported efficiently on a recurring basis. 

> How will we know that our solution is successful?

See above.

> Users

ATD TDS staff; DSD transportation reviewers and staff who issue Building permits

> Sponsorship

Upal Barua

> Which Strategic Direction 2023 “Mobility” indicators would this new application impact?

['System efficiency and congestion']

> Which Austin Strategic Mobility Plan goals would this new application support?

['Commuter Delay – Reduce the amount of time workers spend traveling between home and work.', 'Travel Choice — Promote a balanced transportation network and the ability to make informed choices based on personal needs and preferences.']

> Describe any workarounds you currently have in place or alternative solutions you've considered.

The most basic solution would be to add a fee code or codes in AMANDA for the Street Impact Fee and the calculation would occur elsewhere. One key question is whether we want to program AMANDA to do the calculation. 

> Is there anything else we should know?

Fee collections beginning June 2022, but we know lead time is needed for AMANDA programming. We also need to define the work flow and data needs for reporting.

> How have other divisions/departments/cities addressed similar challenges? 

Austin Water has had an impact fee program for water and wastewater infrastructure for 30 years. They currently use AMANDA and AIMS for their reporting, which occurs quarterly for their Executive Team and twice a year as a public report for the Impact Fee Advisory Committee, which is mandated by the state for all impact fee programs. Jonathan Orenstein's group at AW interacts the most with DSD and AMANDA. I'll be reaching out to him to get more information about their processes.

> Requested By
Liane C.

title: SIF Calculation Process Infos & Functionality (Ready for PROD Deployment)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Feature, Need: 1-Must Have, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT, Project: Street Impact Fee Implimentation
body:
Acceptance Criteria:

- Two new Process infos need to be inserted in the SIF Calculation Process. 

-- Description: SIF Building#
-- Type: AlphaNumeric

-- Description: SIF Invoice Amount 
-- Type: Numeric

- The following validations must be added to the 'Final Calculation' attempt in the SIF calculation process.

-- Pre-condition: System must not allow the user to save the attempt if the process infos SIF Building # and SIF Invoice Amount do not have a value. 
-- Post-Action: System should insert ATD - Street Impact Fee in the Fee tab with the fee amount provided in SIF Invoice Amount Process info and GL Account number chosen based on SIF District Folder Info and bill the fee. 
-- Post-Action: System must also clear the values present in the SIF Building # and SIF Invoice Amount Process Infos. 
-- Post-Action: System must add Building number provided in the SIF Building # process info to the AccountBillFeeComment column of the Fee.

labels: Type: Feature, Need: 1-Must Have, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
**Email from Ryan M. 4/25/22:**

The City Council will be considering an item on May 5 that will allow us to begin charging emergency permit application fees. If passed, we would want to begin assessing this fee ASAP. It already exists in the fee schedule and I think the work was done in AMANDA, but we just need to enable it. What would the timeline look like to enable if it’s passed on 5/5?

**Acceptance Criteria** 

- **RW TURP Emergency Permit fee -  Fee amount - 95$ -- GL A/C: 5125 2400 9100 4087** 

-- System should insert the TURP New Permit fee in an RW folder if the work type is NOT Franchised Utility and 'Emergency' info is NO (This feature may already exist) 

-- System should insert the TURP Emergency Permit fee in an RW folder if the work type is NOT Franchised Utility and 'Emergency' info is YES (This is a new feature) 

-- TURP Emergency Permit Fee should also be available to add through the Insert and Run fee procedure. 

**EX Excavation Application fee - Emergency - Fee amount - 95$ -- GL A/C: 5125 2400 9100 4057** 

-- System should insert Excavation new permit fee in the EX folder if subtype is not franchised utility and Info fields 'Emergency' and 'Secondary' are 'NO' (This feature may already exist)

-- System should insert Excavation application fee - Secondary in the EX folder if subtype is not franchised utility and Info fields 'Emergency' is answered 'NO' and 'Secondary' is answered 'YES' (This feature may already exist)

-- System should insert Excavation application fee - Emergency in the EX folder if subtype is not franchised utility and Info fields 'Emergency' is answered 'YES' and 'Secondary' is answered 'YES' (This is a new feature)

-- The Excavation Application Fee - Emergency should also be available to insert through the Insert and Run Fee procedure.

title: (EPIC) OSE Folder Process Cleanup (On PROD🎉🎉) (Waiting a Week to close)
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Type: Feature, Need: 3-Could Have, Epic, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
## As an OSE reviewer, I need the folder processes updated to add more value and efficiency to our AMANDA usage. I would like to have the Processes, their attempt results and what those processes and attempts do to the folder reviewed to better fit our workflow.

**Stakeholder:** Maria A.
**DTS Manager:** Nate

**Acceptance Criteria:**
**This will apply to the RW SubType: Street Event (50510)**

- Customer applies online/submits
- System inserts process 7000 Web Acceptance (Same; no changes)
- Upon saving 'Accepted' attempt on Web Acceptance the system will:
  -  Update the folder status to ‘Pending’
  -  Insert processes Event Review (50560), Event Intake (50555), Activity Log (80115) and Event Billed (new)
- Event Review (50560) should **not** add any fees when inserted
- **Remove** the "Event Intake" Process (50555)
- **Remove** the "Activity Log" Process (80115)
----




- **(50560) ‘Event Review’** - Attempts: Approved, Awaiting Update, Expired, Rejected, Send Notification Letter, Withdrawn, Cancelled (new)
    -  Is assigned to ‘**_ACE ATD Reviewer_**’ group
    -  ‘Cancelled’ (new) will close the ‘Event Review’ process, update the process status to **_‘Closed’_**, and updates the folder status to **_‘Cancelled’_**
    -  ‘Approved’ changes the folder status to **_‘Pending’_** and closes the process. **_Inserts_** ‘Event Billed’ and ‘Event Permitting’ processes
    -  ‘Awaiting Update’ = **_Please remove_**
    -  ‘Expired’ = **_Please remove_**
    -  ‘Rejected’ changes the folder status to **_‘Rejected’_** and closes the process. **Requires a comment.**
    -  ‘Send Notification Letter’ = **_Please remove_**
    -  ‘Withdrawn’ changes the folder status to **_‘Withdrawn’_** and closes the process. **Requires a comment.**
    -  ‘Cancelled’ changes folder status to **_'Cancelled'_** and closes the process. **Requires a comment.**
-  The Process Date fields should work in the following way:
    -  In Date = The date the process was inserted
    -  Start Date = The date the process was closed
    -  End Date = The date of the start date of the event
## 

- **‘Event Billed’ (New)** is inserted in a **_‘Pending’_** status - Attempts: Billed, Reminder, Cancelled, Paid, Waived
    -  The ‘assigned to’ should be the assigned user
    -  ‘Billed’ will send the customer an email with bill information
        -  Email goes to folder applicant’s Internet User, parent record’s email address
        -  Keeps folder in **_‘Pending’_** status
        - The email verbiage sent to the applicant should be:
          - From Email: 
               - (assigned user, aka whoever created the attempt)
          - To Email: 
               - (applicant email)
          - Subject Line:
              - ACE App. Update: Austin Transportation Special Events Fees Invoiced for [FOLDERNAME]
          - Message Intro:
              - Hello,  
          -  Project Details (Message):
             -  Street Event fees for event [FOLDERNAME] have been billed.  
             -  You can pay online by Check or Credit Card by visiting https://abc.austintexas.gov. Go to 'My Bills' to view and pay your pending invoices.   
             -  Please reach out if you have any additional questions. 
             - Austin Transportation 
             - Austin Center for Events

- ‘Reminder’ will send the customer an email with bill information
    -  Email goes to folder applicant's Internet User, parent record's email address
    -  Keeps folder in **_‘Pending’_** status
    -  The email verbiage sent to the applicant should be:
          - From Email: 
               - (assigned user, aka whoever created the attempt)
          - To Email: 
               - (applicant email)
          - Subject Line:
              - ACE App. Update: Austin Transportation Special Events Fees Invoiced for [FOLDERNAME]
          - Message Intro:
              - Hello,  
          -  Project Details (Message):
             -  ** Street Event fees for event [FOLDERNAME] have already been billed. ** 
             -  You can pay online by Check or Credit Card by visiting https://abc.austintexas.gov. Go to 'My Bills' to view and pay your pending invoices.   
             -  Please reach out if you have any additional questions. 
             - Austin Transportation 
             - Austin Center for Events
-  ‘Cancelled’ will **_close_** the process ("Event Billed") and update the folder status to **_‘Cancelled’_**
-  ‘Waived’ will: **_close_** the process ("Event Billed") and update the folder status to **_‘Pending’_** and** insert process (50560) ‘Event Permitting’
-  ‘Paid’ will **close** the process ("Event Billed") update folder status to **_'Pending'_, and** insert process (50560) ‘Event Permitting’
-  The Process Date fields should work in the following way:
    -  In Date = The date the process was inserted
    -  Start Date = The date the process was closed
    -  End Date = The date of the start date of the event
##

-  **  (50560) ‘Event Permitting**’– Attempts: Approved, Rejected, Cancelled, Withdrawn
    -  This process **is mandatory for permit issuance** (process must be closed before permit issues)
    -  Folder status should stay as **_“Pending”_** until an attempt is entered
    -  The ‘assigned to’ should be the assigned user
    -  Attempts:
        -  'Approved' will: **close** the Process and update the folder status to **_'Pending Permit'_**
        -  'Rejected' will: **close** the Process and update the folder status to **_'Rejected'_**
        -  'Cancelled' will: **close** the Process and update the folder status to **_'Cancelled'_**
        -  'Withdrawn' will: **close** the Process and update the folder status to **_'Withdrawn'_**
    -  **Remove** **_‘Customer Contacted’_** attempt
-  The Process Date fields should work in the following way:
    -  In Date = The date the process was inserted
    -  Start Date = The date the process was closed
    -  End Date = The date of the start date of the event

**Notes on current workflow (Just Informational):**
Once a RW SE Folder gets created in AMANDA or via Portal, it goes into an Event Intake process as "Pending"
Once an attempt of "Accepted"/"Approved" gets placed in the Event Intake Process (Assigned to the ROW Intake Group) the status becomes "Pending ", Cancelled , Withdrawn, Rejected closes the process and folder.
It then creates a new Process called "Event Review" (50560) and inserts a fee that they delete anyways because it is paid by the time they have reviewed the folder.
Then the Permit is issued.

**Link to meeting recording:**
https://web.microsoftstream.com/video/a73eadba-f746-4d23-b1bf-9afd2d7e2de2

title: AMANDA Report: Unpaid fees (TL)

body:
## **As a user i'd like the system to pull up the list of unpaid fees when i submit a query.**

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim P., Ryan M.
**DTS Manager:** Tracy

**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. System should send an email to rightofway@austintexas.gov on the 1st of every month containing the ATD Unpaid Fees Report for the previous month as an attachment. This needs to be done through batch process.
2. User should be able to generate the ATD Unpaid Fees Report manually from the Reports tab in AMANDA.
3. When a user manually generates the ATD Unpaid Fees Report, they should be able to provide From and To date ranges as a parameter.
4. The report should contain any unpaid fee, billed or unbilled from the following folders:
               - DS
               - EX
               - LC
               - PSM 
               - PSM
               - ECV Folder type with subtype ATD (ONLY)
               - GF folder type with subtype ATD (ONLY)
5. The report should primarily be sorted by Folder type and secondarily be sorted by subtype and by Bill number, with unbilled fees at the end of each of folder type
6. The report needs to contain the following columns in the defined order below: 
              - Folder type
              - Subtype 
              - FolderRSN 
              - Bill Number
              - Fee amount
7. The report should also contain totals by folder type, total billed fees by folder type and total unbilled fees by folder type
8. The generated report must be of .csv format
9. The report format should look like this: 
![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5f50fe1f66d1a40f7f557fb4/50047297-b821-4437-b529-13dacbe71796)

**Notes:**
- There is an existing report in the ATD library (56110). This query probably needs to be updated.
- If the existing fee report can't be updated to match the requirements, then once the new report has been created, the previous one (56110) needs to be removed. 
 
- Tracy has a lot of unpaid fee queries that may be useful

Per email from Paloma, see #2381

title: Project: AMANDA FY23 Fee Updates
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Workgroup: ROW, Type: Feature, Impact: 1-Severe, Service: Product, Need: 1-Must Have, Epic, Type: Enhancement, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Project Index, Product: AMANDA Portal
body:
Implementation of ATD FY23 fee schedule updates for fees maintained in the [AMANDA System](https://github.com/cityofaustin/atd-data-tech/issues/4790)

## Background

The city's yearly [Budgeting Process](https://financeonline.austintexas.gov/afo/afo_content.cfm?s=1&p=57), Department Fee schedules, Fee Logic/Workflow and Fee amounts have to be updated in AMANDA, if it has an applicable change, by September 30, 2022 and Go live date of October 01, 2022. With this being a large public facing project, it will require a Project Based approach to be delivered on time and to specs.

## Scope & Deliverables

_**In Scope:**_
-  Updating the AMANDA Budgeting Processes, Department Fee schedules, Fee Logic/Workflow and Fee amounts have to be updated in AMANDA, allowing staff to be able to Process approved FY23 fees in AMANDA.
- Budgeting Process, Department Fee schedules, Fee Logic/Workflow and Fee amounts have to be updated in AMANDA, if it has an applicable change, by September 30, 2022 and Go live on October 01, 2022.

_**Out of Scope:**_
- Fees on the fee schedule that are not, or should not be maintained in AMANDA are out of scope. 
- Any non-AMANDA solutions are also out of scope.

_**Constraints/RoadBlocks:**_
    - CTM's V7 Upgrade Project
    - Payment connections between AMANDA and CityBase
    - Testing payments on V7
    - Changes to FY22 fees must go live on Oct1 2022 only and cannot impact current PROD environment and its fees

## Desired Outcomes
-  All updated AMANDA Budgeting Processes, Department Fee schedules, Fee Logic/Workflow and Fee amounts will be UATd and verified properly prior to and after implementation.
- 2-3 week stabilization period for any changes
- All new fees and their changes are implemented properly and working on Oct 01, 2022
Impact this project can have, success metrics

## Timebox

All changes to fees must and will be implemented by September 30th, 2022 and go Live on October 01, 2022

**_Components:_**

Scoping: April - May
Technical requirements and documentation: May - June
System development: June - July
User acceptance testing: July - August
Training and implementation: September

## Concepts and references

- OSE FY23 Fees are [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1sZchwEo_qq54bh4F9nnEuXBukXaktoJm/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=114042363287535953312&rtpof=true&sd=true)

title: OSE Folder Process Cleanup; Initial and Event Review Process (On PROD🎉🎉)
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Type: Feature, Need: 3-Could Have, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
## As an OSE reviewer, I need the folder processes updated to add more value and efficiency to our AMANDA usage. I would like to have the Processes, their attempt results and what those processes and attempts do to the folder reviewed to better fit our workflow.

**Stakeholder:** Maria A.
**DTS Manager:** Nate

**Acceptance Criteria:**
**This will apply to the RW SubType: Street Event (50510)**

- Customer applies online/submits
- System inserts process 7000 Web Acceptance (Same; no changes)
- Upon saving 'Accepted' attempt on Web Acceptance the system will:
  -  Update the folder status to ‘Pending’
  -  Insert processes Event Review (50560) and Event Billed (new)
- Event Review (50560) should **not** add any fees when inserted
- If it is from Backoffice submission, only Event Review (50560) process must be added
- **Remove** the "Event Intake" Process (50555)
- **Remove** the "Activity Log" Process (80115)

- **(50560) ‘Event Review’** - Attempts: Approved, Awaiting Update, Expired, Rejected, Send Notification Letter, Withdrawn, Cancelled (new)
    -  Is assigned to ‘**_ACE ATD Reviewer_**’ group
    -  ‘Cancelled’ (new) will close the ‘Event Review’ process, update the process status to **_‘Closed’_**, and updates the folder status to **_‘Cancelled’_**
    -  ‘Approved’ changes the folder status to **_‘Pending’_** and closes the process. **_Inserts_** ‘Event Billed’ (only for backoffice submission) and ‘Event Permitting’ processes
    -  ‘Awaiting Update’ = **_Please remove_** (Only for Subtype Street Event)
    -  ‘Expired’ = **_Please remove_** (Only for Subtype Street Event)
    -  ‘Rejected’ changes the folder status to **_‘Rejected’_** and closes the process. **Requires a comment.**
    -  ‘Send Notification Letter’ = **_Please remove_** (Only for Subtype Street Event)
    -  ‘Withdrawn’ changes the folder status to **_‘Withdrawn’_** and closes the process. **Requires a comment.**
    -  ‘Cancelled’ changes folder status to **_'Cancelled'_** and closes the process. **Requires a comment.**
-  The Process Date fields should work in the following way:
    -  In Date = The date the process was inserted
    -  Start Date = The date the process was closed
    -  End Date = The date of the start date of the event

title: OSE Folder Process Cleanup; Event Billed Process (New) (On PROD🎉🎉)
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Need: 3-Could Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
## As an OSE reviewer, I need the folder processes updated to add more value and efficiency to our AMANDA usage. I would like to have the Processes, their attempt results and what those processes and attempts do to the folder reviewed to better fit our workflow.

**Stakeholder:** Maria A.
**DTS Manager:** Nate

**Acceptance Criteria:**
**This will apply to the RW SubType: Street Event (50510)**
- **‘Event Billed’ (New)** is inserted in a **_‘Pending’_** status - Attempts: Billed, Reminder, Cancelled, Paid, Waived
    -  The ‘assigned to’ should be the assigned user
    -  ‘Billed’ will send the customer an email with bill information
        -  Email goes to folder applicant’s Internet User, parent record’s email address
        -  Keeps folder in **_‘Pending’_** status
        - The email verbiage sent to the applicant should be:
          - From Email: 
               - (assigned user, aka whoever created the attempt)
          - To Email: 
               - (applicant email)
          - Subject Line:
              - ACE App. Update: Austin Transportation Special Events Fees Invoiced for [FOLDERNAME]
          - Message Intro:
              - Hello,  
          -  Project Details (Message):
             -  Street Event fees for event [FOLDERNAME] have been billed.  
             -  You can pay online by Check or Credit Card by visiting https://abc.austintexas.gov. Go to 'My Bills' to view and pay your pending invoices.   
             -  Please reach out if you have any additional questions. 
             - Austin Transportation 
             - Austin Center for Events

- ‘Reminder’ will send the customer an email with bill information
    -  Email goes to folder applicant's Internet User, parent record's email address
    -  Keeps folder in **_‘Pending’_** status
    -  The email verbiage sent to the applicant should be:
          - From Email: 
               - (assigned user, aka whoever created the attempt)
          - To Email: 
               - (applicant email)
          - Subject Line:
              - ACE App. Update: Austin Transportation Special Events Fees Invoiced for [FOLDERNAME]
          - Message Intro:
              - Hello,  
          -  Project Details (Message):
             -  ** Street Event fees for event [FOLDERNAME] have already been billed. ** 
             -  You can pay online by Check or Credit Card by visiting https://abc.austintexas.gov. Go to 'My Bills' to view and pay your pending invoices.   
             -  Please reach out if you have any additional questions. 
             - Austin Transportation 
             - Austin Center for Events
-  ‘Cancelled’ will **_close_** the process ("Event Billed") and update the folder status to **_‘Cancelled’_**
-  ‘Waived’ will: **_close_** the process ("Event Billed") and update the folder status to **_‘Pending’_
-  ‘Paid’ will **close** the process ("Event Billed") update folder status to **_'Pending'_
-  The Process Date fields should work in the following way:
    -  In Date = The date the process was inserted
    -  Start Date = The date the process was closed
    -  End Date = The date of the start date of the event

title: BUG: Resolve invoices issue
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Bug Report, Impact: 3-Minor, Product: AMANDA
body:
_Submitted by Paloma_
<!-- Email -->
<!-- paloma.amayo-ryan@austintexas.gov -->

### As the system, I need to email the folder applicant a copy of the permit when the bill is paid online. 
### As the system, when multiple bills are paid online, I need to email the folder applicant a copy of the permit for each folder/permit that was paid.

The Acceptance Criteria provided below applies to all DS, RW and EX folders: 

- When user pays for multiple invoices at the same time through the My Bills page on Portal, system must attach each permit paid to an email and send the email to the user. 
- Currently, system sends email for each invoice paid. But, only the first Permit document is sent multiple times. For example, if customer pays 6 invoices in one transaction, they get 6 copies of the first permit. 
- This functionality needs to be validated for different invoices from all folders.  


> What application are you using?

AMANDA

> Describe the problem.

When applicants go to pay a bulk of invoices (I believe AMANDA allows people to pay up to 25 invoices in one transaction), they are allowed to pay all and all permits that were paid for become active but it only send the applicant the permit associated with the first invoice in the “queue” to pay. And it sends them as many copies as invoices. For example, if they pay 6 invoices in one transaction, they get 6 copies of that first permit. This is causing me to go back in and manually email those permits to applicants, thus, taking time away from other reviews. As events start picking up post-COVID shutdown, I see this being a persistent and growing problem as many of these permits usually get inputted, reviewed, and issued in bulk. 

> Is there anything else we should know?

This issue has been reported for DS and Parking permits.  I suspect it is effecting all folder types.  

Additional info regarding this has been forwarded to Kimberly P and Isabell P.  (I'm out of the office starting now through July 19th. Woohoo!)

> Website Address

n/a

> Requested By
Paloma A.

title: Suspend Permit Folders When Contractor License Expires
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Feature, Need: 3-Could Have, Product: AMANDA
body:
### When an LC folder expires, we'd like the system to identify the related active permit folders, and update the folder status to 'Suspended'. 

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim
**DTS Manager:** TBD

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- System should run a daily batch that checks to find LC folders that are 9 days away from expiry, and send an email to 'Right-Of-Way Contractor' of those LC folders if they are associated with any 'Active' status DS or EX folders. 
- System should send an email for each 'Active' DS or EX folder the Right of Way Contractor is associated with
- Text for the email
 
Subject: ROW Permit Expiration Notice

Dear Michael Miller *(Right-Of-Way Contractor People record First Name and Last Name)*, 

This email is to advise you that your permit # 2020-140984 EX *(Associated DS or EX Permit Number)* for 605 W 4TH ST *(Primary Property Address of associated DS or EX Permit)* will be expired due to your Concrete License 2007-123456 LC *(LC folder Permit number)* expiry on 12/31/2020 *(LC folder expiry date)* . To renew your Concrete License, email current versions of your documents to rightofway@austintexas.gov. For further information, click on the link below: 
https://austintexas.gov/page/right-way-contractors 

- System should run a daily batch that checks for LC folders that have a status of 'Expired'. 
- System should then check the People record of LC folders that have a type of 'Right-Of-Way Contractor' to see if they are part of any DS or EX folders 
- If there are any DS or EX folders for the People record that have a status of 'Active', system should change the folder status of these folders to 'Expired - License'
- System should also check daily if any LC folders have changed from 'Expired' to 'Active'
- If there are any LC folders that are now 'Active', system should change the corresponding DS and EX folders from 'Expired - License' to 'Active'  

**Note** - The status 'Expired-License' does not exist currently. It needs to be newly created. 
**Note** - As an extension to this feature, it was also suggested that the insurance dates can be considered to expire DS and EX folders. This may be addressed as a separate ticket after this one is implemented.

n/a

title: Automate RW-Parking (Load/Unload) Approval Fees
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 2-Should Have, Epic, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As a ROW Permit Analyst, I want the system to insert the correct approval fees on the RW Parking Spaces (Load/Unload) folder

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim
**DTS Manager:** TBD

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Info field 'Number of after hours of service' (Info code 75947) should be removed from any RW folder (Currently exists, needs to be removed)
- Users should be able to see a new info field 'Rate if metered (in $ per parking meter)' (No infocode exists, needs to be added) in RW folders of subtype Parking Spaces and worktype Load/Unload
- System should insert the Parking Space Permit Fee (50170) when 'Approved' attempt is made in Parking Parking Review Process (50662) in RW folder of subtype Parking Spaces and worktype Load/Unload 
- System should also create a bill when the Parking Space Permit Fee (50170) is inserted in Right of Way folder of subtype Parking Spaces (Fee code exists, logic needs to be updated)
- The amount for Parking Space Permit Fee should be calculated as follows:
Metered Fee = Value in Info Rate if metered (in $ per parking meter)   **X**   Value in 'Number of Days' Info field (Info Code 75390)  **X**   16   **X**   Number of 'Parking Spaces : Meter Number' Rows in Property & Street Information Freeform 
Unmetered Fee = 3.20   **X**   Value in 'Number of Days' Info field (Info Code 75390)   **X**   Value in 'Number of (#)' field in 'Parking Spaces : # Unmetered Spaces' row of Property & Street Information Freeform
Parking Space Permit Fee (50170) = Metered Fee + Unmetered Fee

**Note** 
- '**X**' in the payment logic above denotes multiplication
- Values 16 and 3.20 are variables and may change in the future. These should not be hard coded and should be added to a lookup table (Tracy mentioned this was lookup table 5025)
- The logic for inserting the fee may currently exist. If it does, it needs to be updated or removed to account for this new change in logic
- A screenshot of Property & Street Information Freeform provided below for reference

labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 3-Could Have, Epic, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As a ROW Permit Analyst, I need AMANDA to record insurance and bond information for Responsible Parties. 

### As a ROW Permit Analyst, I need the RW-TURP folder to validate that the bond & insurance info for the responsible party people record is current.

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim
**DTS Manager:** Tracy

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- **On people type 'Responsible Party', create 9 new people infos**
    - Bond Company Name (text)
    - Bond Status (boolean: Active, Expired, Suspended)
    - Bond Number (text)
    - Bond Expiration Date (date mm/dd/yyyy)
    - Insurance Company Name (test)
    - Insurance Status (boolean: Active, Expired, Suspended)
    - Insurance Policy Number (text)
    - Insurance Effective Date (date mm/dd/yyyy)
    - Insurance Expiration Date (date mm/dd/yyyy)


**On RW, Temporary Right of Way Use:**
- Create new folder issue validation rule(s)
    - People type 'Responsible Party' is on the people tab
    - If 'Responsible Party' people type is found, perform people record info validations:
    1. Insurance & Bond Expiration Dates: If dates are in the past, do not allow folder issuance
    2. Insurance & Bond Status: If either value is not Active, do not allow folder issuance
    - If 'Responsible Party' people type is not found, look for 'Right of Way Contractor'. If found, issue the folder.
    - If 'Right of Way Contractor' people type is not found, look for 'City Department'. If found, issue the folder.
    - If 'City Department' is not found, look for 'Franchised Utility' people type. If found, issue the folder. If not found, do not allow folder issuance.
    - _Stakeholders are open to not performing these validations and instead inserting dummy info for the bond/insurance exceptions like City Departments and Franchised Utility._ 
    3. Shift the Bond/Insurance infos validation to Issue code.
    4.  Bond/Insurance infos must **NOT** be made mandatory

title: Bug: Process Status should reflect the attempt result made (NN)
labels: Type: Bug Report, Impact: 3-Minor, Need: 2-Should Have, Workgroup: CPO, Product: AMANDA
body:
### **As A Corridor Program Office folder Reviewer, I have noticed that the Status of the Mobility Bond Review Process defaults to closed no matter the result when it should reflect the process attempt that was made.**

The Status of the Mobility Bond Review Process (51093) defaults to closed no matter the attempt result.  This happens on Small Cell Permit and ROW Permit Folders.  On Land Management Folders the Status drop down reflects the result. This is a manual change to the drop down each time. This function is important for the Small Cell Permit Folders due to the fact that the applicant receives a Master Comment Report and the status needs to be reflected.

**Examples:**
ROW Permit – RSN 12542816
Small Cell Permit – RSN 12540296
Land Management – RSN 12545694


**Stakeholders:** Jessica Davis
DTS Manager: Nate

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- System should automatically update the Process status of Mobility Bond Review Process (51093) to match with the attempt result made in the Process for ROW and Small Cell Permits 
For example, if user makes 'Approved' attempt in the process, Process Status needs to be automatically updated to 'Approved'

**Note** - This works for Land Management Permits, but not for ROW and Small Cell Permits

And then would like to standardized the naming of fees across all of these menus.

> Describe the outcome you'd like to see when this feature is implemented.

This will ensure we are assessing fees accurately and consistently, benefiting our customers and our department.  (Avoids over or under collection.)

> Describe any workarounds you currently have in place or alternative solutions you've considered.

We add fees via the Insert menu but that requires knowing the fee name or code.  Some fees are named so similarly that it can be difficult to discern which is the correct one to assess.

> Requested By
Paloma A.

title: Update EX Extension Granted & Create COS Payment Automation (Passed PROD UAT)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 2-Should Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT, Project: FY22 AMANDA Fee Updates
body:
### Updates to Right-of-Way Admin Process - Extension Granted Attempt

**Overview:**
In order to implement Cost of Service payment automation on excavation extension fees, the workflow and features of the AMANDA extension features must be updated. 

**Workflow / Acceptance Criteria:**

Role | Task
-- | --
User | Saves attempt 'Extension Granted'
System | Performs Validations:✔️Process Infos are entered: New Start Date, New End Date✔️Folder issue date must exist✔️ROW Contractor must exist & be active
System | Updates Right-of-Way Admin Process infos values to NULL for next extension.
System | Inserts extenion comment in folder description.
System | Copies process infos to folder infos: - New Start Date  ➡️Extension Start Date - New End Date ➡️ Extension End Date
System: | ❓Decision: Is this Franchise, COS, or Private/Project Connect?
  |  
  | 🔹 FRANCHISE 🔹
System | ✔️Update folder status to Active✔️Update folder expiration date to info 'Extension End Date'
  |  
  | 🔹 COS 🔹
System | ❓Decision: Is info Secondary yes or no?
System | IF YES:   ✔️Insert Fees: Excavation Permit Fee - Secondary, ATD Tech Surcharge ROW✔️Create bill✔️Pay bill with COS payment type - (A.U.P. triggered by payment)
System | IF NO:   ✔️Insert Fees: Excavation Permit Fee - Extension, ATD Tech Surcharge ROW✔️Create bill✔️Pay bill with COS payment type - (A.U.P. triggered by payment)
  |  
  | 🔹 PRIVATE DEVELOPER / PROJECT CONNECT 🔹
System | ❓Decision: Is info Secondary yes or no?
System | IF YES:✔️Insert Fees: Excavation Permit Fee - Secondary, ROW Usage Fee(s), ATD Tech Surcharge ROW - (do not create bill)
System | IF NO:✔️Insert Fees: Excavation Permit Fee - Extension, ROW Usage Fee(s), ATD Tech Surcharge ROW - (do not create bill)
  | ⛔️ STOP/DONE



----


![Excavation Extension Granted](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/146278522-93f6fd94-876f-41b0-a10b-3a64380cad8a.jpg)

![Activate Upon Payment](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/146278559-8f285466-2b6b-4bcd-b257-5287aa9de448.jpg)

title: Fee Logic Updates to TURP & EX (On PROD 🎉🎉)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Impact: 1-Severe, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT, Project: FY22 AMANDA Fee Updates
body:
# This single issue covers the development for removing old fee logic and implementing new fee logic on the RW-TURP & EX permits. 




## [TURP](https://app.zenhub.com/workspaces/data--technology-services-5caf7dc6ecad11531cc418ef/issues/cityofaustin/atd-data-tech/6564)

### Remove the following functionality:
- [ ] The current fee insertion and work type selection triggers for RW-TURP folders need to be removed as they are all going to change (#4469, #6322) . Provided below are some places where these triggers have been identified. Make sure Extension Fee inserts based on Property & Street Information irrespective of the WorkType: PVT Long Term

- [ ] Info field Event Start Date (75980) and Event End Date (75985) determine appropriate work type for the folder. This functionality needs to be removed.
- [ ] Any functionality based on Info field Project Sponsor (76765) needs to be removed.


### Create new fee logic for the fees provided below:

- [ ] **TURP New Permit Fee**

- Applies only when sub type is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.
- This fee needs to be added when a new application is created either from portal or back office
- Fee needs to be added only if folder Info 'Emergency' (#6641) is answered 'No'.
-Applicant must pay this fee before folder status updates to Internet Pending


- [ ] **TURP Extension Permit Fee**

- Currently the system inserts TURP ROW fees for extensions when attempt 'Extension Granted' is made in Permit Extension Process (50680).
- System needs to insert the TURP Permit Extension Fee at this trigger along with other fees.
- Applies only when work type is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.



----
## [EX](https://app.zenhub.com/workspaces/data--technology-services-5caf7dc6ecad11531cc418ef/issues/cityofaustin/atd-data-tech/6565)

### Remove the following functionality:
_The following fee procedures and logic need to be removed for the EX fees:_

- [ ] The Excavation/Concrete Permit fee - Transport (50348) is inserted when application is created through Portal. This fee insertion needs to be removed.


### Create new fee logic for the fees provided below:

- [ ] **Excavation Permit Fee - New**
- Applies only when worktype is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.
- This fee needs to be added when a new application is created either from portal or back office.
- This fee should be added only if Info field 'Emergency' (#6641) and Info field 'Secondary' (#6321) are answered 'No'
- Applicant must pay this fee before folder status updates to Internet Pending.

- [ ] **Excavation Application Fee - Secondary - $95**
- Applies only when work type is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.
- Fee needs to be added only if folder Info 'Secondary' (#6321) is answered 'Yes' and Folder Info 'Emergency' is answered 'No'.
- This fee needs to be added when a new application is created either from portal or back office
- Applicant must pay this fee before folder status updates to Internet Pending



- [ ] **Excavation Application Fee - Extension - $175**
- This fee should be inserted manually when user navigates to fee tab and clicks Add->Insert.
- The manually inserted fee should be inserted with the fee amount of $175.
- Applies only when subtype is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.


----

title: Project: ROWMAN Phase 4
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Service: Product, Epic, Product: AMANDA
body:
Phase 4 of the ROWMAN Replacement Project aims to provide staff and the public with real time permitted road closure data. 

## Background
Construction related road closure permits often give the contractor an approved timeframe for closing the road. For example, ATD may give a contractor 7 calendar days to perform 2 days of work. As such, it is impossible to know when a contractor is actually in the right of way. This hinders ATD’s ability to coordinate activity in the Right of Way, and it impacts the traveling public’s ability to plan their routes. 

Due to the nature of construction, giving the contractor a ‘window’ is necessary, so we must design a solution that allows for us to continue giving them a window and will also allow us to gather data from the contractor on-site, when they are closing and re-opening the Right of Way. 

## Scope & Deliverables
**This project includes:**
- Updating internal permitting workflows to include processes that will make real-time road closure data possible.
- Building a customer-facing solution for permit holders that will allow them to easily notify ATD when they begin a road closure, and when they end it. 
- Designing the real-time road closure data to conform with Work Zone Data Exchange specifications.
- Publishing this data for public use, especially for existing public mapping tools like Google Maps and Waze

## Desired Outcomes
Success for this project means city staff, permit analysts, right of way coordinators, and the public will have access to real-time permitted road closure information. This will reduce the amount of permitting conflicts in the Right-of-Way, which, when they happen, have adverse effects on the contractor’s ability to perform their work and can cause unnecessary traffic congestion. This will also allow the public to better plan their routes and avoid delays caused by permitted road closures. 

We also hope that by openly publishing this data, companies that provide mapping products will be able to integrate this data into their product and provide their users with real-time closure data. 


## Timebox
This is a complex project with heavy scoping/analysis needs. While we have already performed much of the scoping, we will need to refresh the analysis when the project is picked up. 

**Expected Timeline:**

- Scoping & Analysis: 1 Month
- Review Possible Solutions: 1 Month
- Writing Requirements and Acceptance Criteria: 2 Weeks
- Development: 1-2 Months
- Testing: 1 Month
- Training Staff & Permit Holders: 1 Month
- Total Duration From Start to Go-Live: **6 Months**

---
This Github issue represents a project of Austin Transportation's [Data & Technology Services](https://product.austinmobility.io/) team. Project status is documented regularly in the comments below.

title: Request Changes to the Public Space Management (PSM) folder in AMANDA
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 2-Should Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA
body:
<!-- Email -->
<!-- paloma.amayo-ryan@austintexas.gov -->

**Acceptance Criteria**

- There needs to be a new attachment type added to PSM folders called 'Application'. 
- This new attachment type must be visible both in the portal and the Back Office. 


- User should be able to submit attachments through the portal after the permit application has been submitted
- This currently happens in the DS and EX folders. PSM needs to have the same functionality. 

- When adding a new People record to a PSM folder in the back office, user must be able to choose from all available People types. Currently only the Applicant option is shown. 
- This works correctly in RW-TURP folder, for reference. 

- Info code 86110 should be changed to: Historic Designation Approval - 6th Street from IH-35 to Lavaca Street. 



> What application are you using?

AMANDA

> Describe the problem.

The Public Space Management (PSM) folder in AMANDA + ABC Portal needs a few tweaks.  (Some of these may be bugs not identified during original development of folder.)  PSM needs are:
- Add an Attachment option for "Application"
- Allow portal users to attach documents after application submittal
- Allow other people records to be added to the Folder tab
- Correct the boundaries listed under the Historic Designation field in the portal application

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5e8dfbfabf171441c3a5684e/d5fca065-ca16-4e12-9055-f165f68b2b74)


> Describe the outcome you'd like to see when this feature is implemented.

Our team *and* our customers will encounter a more functional/efficient PSM folder.

> Describe any workarounds you currently have in place or alternative solutions you've considered.

For the attachment issues, customers must email the Permit Analyst who then attaches documents on their behalf.  (Which is burdensome when you consider the fact that the customers rarely know which Permit Analyst to email.)

For the other people records there is no work around so we are collecting incomplete data.

For the historic designation issues there is no work around so customers are seeing incorrect information (which contradicts the correct info we have published online).

> Is there anything else we should know?

The sooner the better as we are expecting an increase in PSM applications over the coming months.  (A number of businesses are participating in the temporary "Shop the Block" program and hope to transition to our Sidewalk Cafe/Street Patio permit option before that program expires.)

> Requested By
Paloma A.

Current function:

Applicant selects "Save and Finish Later" in the portal, the payment automation for COS works but it is making the status of an incomplete application "Internet Pending" and not sending it to the "My Incomplete Applications" menu.

-  The system will send the incomplete application to the "My Incomplete Applications" menu

title: Project: Inspector Prioritization Automation
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Service: Product, Project: Inspector Prioritization Automation, Product: AMANDA, Project Index
body:
The Inspector Prioritization Automation Project focuses on creating tools to allow Right of Way Management traffic control inspectors to better prioritize their inspection workload based on priorities identified by the division and department.

## Background
An internal city audit performed in 2018 identified the need for ROW’s traffic control inspection group to better prioritize the inspections they perform. On an average day there are over 4,000 active Right-of-Way permits that are eligible for a traffic control inspection. This number far outweighs ATD’s available resources to provide inspections, resulting in a need to prioritize the inspections we choose to perform. 

Right of Way Management has identified key metrics that will allow us to rate inspection priorities based on things such as location, proximity to critical infrastructure, project impact, and the contractor’s history of traffic control violations. 

## Scope & Deliverables
The scope includes developing automated tools that will score permits based on key metrics, and provide the traffic control inspections group with a prioritized list of inspections. Phase 2 of this project may include a dashboard for the inspectors. 

## Desired Outcomes
Success for this project means the traffic control inspectors are better able to identify the highest priority inspections, resulting in our ability to correct deficiencies in our highest impact areas. Deficiency correction provides safer roadways, and better traffic flow. 

---
This Github issue represents a project of Austin Transportation's [Data & Technology Services](https://product.austinmobility.io/) team. Project status is documented regularly in the comments below.

title: (Duplicate) TDS - New Workflow - Development Assessments
labels: Type: Feature, Need: 2-Should Have, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As a TDS Project Manager, I need to charge the TIA Development Assessment fee to an applicant before any formal applications have been submitted. Currently there is no folder in AMANDA that allows me to do this. 

**Stakeholder:** Sangeeta

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- System should allow a user to create a General Fee (GF) folder with the subtype 'Transportation Development Assessment'
- System should automatically insert TIA Development Assessment Fee of amount $1460 when a user creates a GF folder of subtype Transportation Development Assessment
- System should allow the user the ability to proceed WITHOUT adding a Property to GF folder of subtype Transportation Development Assessment when creating a new folder through the Automatic Add Phase.
- System should allow the user to add People records of type 'Applicant' to a GF folder of subtype Transportation Development Assessment 
- System should allow user to make attachment of type 'Amanda Images' in a GF folder of subtype Transportation Development Assessment. (This currently exists in TIA folder) 
- System should allow user to generate merge document of type 'ATD Engineering Review' in a GF folder of subtype Transportation Development Assessment (This currently exists in TIA folder)
- Public Portal User should be able to view and pay the TIA Development Assessment Fee through the AB+C Portal if the user is added as a People record to a GF folder
- Public Portal User should be able to view details of GF folder that they are associated with when they are logged in to the AB+C Portal similar to how other folders are currently displayed in portal. The 2 screenshots below show what information the portal currently displays for other permits. 

![MicrosoftTeams-image(2).png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5f50fe1f66d1a40f7f557fb4/c3357bee-86a7-445d-a204-e62baa766e21)![MicrosoftTeams-image(3).png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5f50fe1f66d1a40f7f557fb4/cc008c9d-f733-467d-b79a-6b583f242636)

title: Feature: AMANDA GF for TDS Pre-Development Assessments
labels: Type: Feature, Need: 1-Must Have, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Provider: CTM, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As a TDS Reviewer, I need an AMANDA feature to invoice customers for TDA Reviews. As a customer, I need to pay the invoice via the AMANDA Portal.
- _**TDA:** A meeting that occurs between TDS staff & a development customer prior to a formal Site Plan submittal, where staff can provide informal consulting on the proposed development._



----
**Stakeholders:** Sangeeta Jain, Amber Hutchens


**Acceptance Criteria** 

- System should allow a user to create new folders in AMANDA Back Office under a new worktype called 'Pre-Dev Assessment' with the 'ATD' subtype in the GF folder. 
- During the Automatic add phase of the folder, the following validations need to be added 
-- Folder Name should be mandatory
-- At least one Property record should be added to the folder
-- Primary People type should be 'Billed to' 
-- At least one People record of type 'Billed to' must be added to the folder. 
-- Initial folder status needs to be 'Pending Payment'.  
- The back office folder created under the work type 'Pre-Dev Assessment' should not have any folder Infos or Processes. 
- When user clicks on Insert and Run Procedure in the Fee tab, system should insert the Transportation Development Assessment (83498) (Amount: $1410) and the ATD Tech Surcharge Fee and create a bill for these fees.
- The inserted fees should be available to pay on the Public Portal for the user associated with the Permit 
- When fees are paid through the portal, system must change the folder status of the GF folder to 'Paid'.

body:

title: Get access to AMANDA read-only database
labels: Type: IT Support, Service: Dev, Product: AMANDA
body:
Get access to AMANDA read replica so that we can extract cost of service (COS) data for reporting.

> Hi Gita and Deanna,
> 
> We have a number of upcoming projects that require us to extract AMANDA data programmatically and post-process it with other tools.
> 
> Most immediately, we need to automate a fund-transfer between ATD and other departments that requires us to extract folder/payment info from AMANDA and pipe it into an AIMS-compatible format.
> 
> Correct me if I'm wrong, but I understand there is an AMANDA read-only replica that we could use to run the queries we need. If that's right, would it be possible for us to get have a service account created so that we can accomplish these tasks? If you prefer to federate access through DB views that would be fine, but we'll at least need access to a staging database to develop our queries.
> 
> Thanks and happy to schedule time to discuss. Just let me know.
> John
>

title: Add an "Emergency?" Yes/No field to the Info Tab of the RW - TURP folders
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT, Project: FY22 AMANDA Fee Updates
body:
<!-- Email -->
<!-- paloma.amayo-ryan@austintexas.gov -->

**Stakeholders**: Paloma, Kim, Isabel
**DTS Manager:** Tracy, Nate

**Acceptance Criteria** 

- A new info field needs to be added to EX and RW-TURP folders.
- Info Description: Emergency?
- Info type: Boolean
- Default Info Value: 'No'
- Info should be Required for Insert and Required for Issue (Is mandatory for folder creation & issuance)
- The new Info field must be displayed on portal as a mandatory field for EX and RW-TURP applications
- The folder info needs to be a part of 'Project Information' Info group, same as #6321 
- The info should have either a link or Help Text to educate customers on what is an Emergency
- The link should open in a new page
   -  The link is below:
https://library.municode.com/tx/austin/codes/code_of_ordinances?nodeId=TIT14USSTPUPR_CH14-11USRI-W_ART2USRI-WCOEXFAINTEUS_SPAGEPR_S14-11-161DE

  -  The EX folder has a link on the infos page on portal (Subha will look at the code)

  -  The Help text is below:

> EMERGENCY OPERATIONS means operations or repairs of facilities to prevent imminent harm to the health, safety, or welfare of persons or property.

**Request information**
> What application are you using?

AMANDA

> Describe the problem.

Add an "Emergency?" Yes/No field to the Info Tab of the RW - TURP folders.  (Both in AMANDA and Portal.)  This field would mirror the one already established on the EX folders.

> Describe the outcome you'd like to see when this feature is implemented.

ROW will use this field to accurately calculate the new permit fees (to be effective 10/01/21) assessed to City Departments.  This will also be a valuable field for other reporting needs.

> Describe any workarounds you currently have in place or alternative solutions you've considered.

We capture a TURP's emergency status using the Priority field on the Folder Tab.  This is being done on the back end by Analysts.  Moving this to the Info Tab will allow it to be entered by the *applicants*.

> Is there anything else we should know?

Yes, 10/01/21.

> Requested By
Paloma A.

Request ID: DTS21-102260

Capital Improvement Projects (CIPs) include projects such as the construction, replacement, renovation, or purchase of **City** assets.  These projects are funded by the Capital Budget (with the exception of projects funded by Austin Energy).

title: Project: Right of Way AMANDA Permitting Metrics
labels: Workgroup: OOD, Workgroup: ROW, Epic, Product: AMANDA, Project Index, Project: ROW Permitting Metrics
body:
Enhancements to the AMANDA permitting system to 1.) Capture Right-of-Way permitting metrics data, and 2.) Create all AMANDA reports requested by ATD Executive Management. 

## Background

ATD Executive Management has requested a series of AMANDA reports related to Right-of-Way permitting and has identified 4 major reporting metrics. Unfortunately the majority of the data required for this reporting does not currently exist. 

## Scope & Deliverables
There will be two (2) phases of development. 

- Phase 1: Update AMANDA permitting folders so the necessary data can be captured.
- Phase 2: Create the reports for our stakeholders.


Desired   Outcome | Deliverables
-- | --
Staff   can create and view data related to permitting turnaround times. | All permit folders updated to   capture dependable application and issuance timestamps.
Staff   can create and view data related to permitting review cycles. | All permit folders workflows are   updated to capture review cycle data.
Staff   can create and view data related to permitting review duration. | All permit folders workflows are   updated to capture data related to duration of reviews.
Staff   can create and view data related to permitting review deficiencies. | All permit folders workflows are   updated to capture data related to permitting deficiencies.
Staff   has access to on-demand reporting for Right-of-Way permitting metrics. | Custom AMANDA permitting metrics   reports are available in the ATD AMANDA Custom Report Library, which is   available to all ATD staff.
Staff   understands the new enhancements and how to use them. | Employee training is provided to   Right-of-Way management.





## Timebox
From kickoff to delivery, we estimate this project will take 4 – 6 months.

**Phase 1: AMANDA Enhancements**

Project   Task | Estimated Time/Duration
-- | --
Scoping | 8 Weeks
Acceptance   Criteria | 1 Week
Development | 6-12 Weeks
User Acceptance Testing | 4-6 Weeks
Staff   Training | 2 Weeks
**Total:** | **21-29 Weeks (7 Months)**



**Phase 2: Custom Reports**

Project   Task | Estimated Time/Duration
-- | --
Scoping | .5 Weeks
Acceptance   Criteria | .5 Weeks
Development | 1 - 3 Weeks
User   Acceptance Testing | 2 Weeks
**Total:** | **4 - 6 Weeks**

title: (Documentation) New TURP Fee Structure & Logic
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Project: FY22 AMANDA Fee Updates
body:
### Dev work will not be done on this issue/ticket. This issue is now for reference only.


**Notes 7/27/21**
- Vish will update the AC
- We will review w/ Sree
- Ask Sree: Which order the work should be done in, and how she would like the work split up into separate issues. 

**Sections/Grouping of Work**
- Removing existing functionality
- Add new fees, update existing fees
- Add new functionality for new fee logic (triggers for fee insertion)



**Acceptance Criteria:** 
**Remove the following functionality:**
The current fee insertion and work type selection triggers for RW-TURP folders need to be removed as they are all going to change (#4469, #6322) . Provided below are some places where these triggers have been identified. 

- Info field Event Start Date (75980) and Event End Date (75985) determine appropriate work type for the folder. This functionality needs to be removed.
- Any functionality based on Info field Project Sponsor (76765) needs to be removed. 

**Configure the following fees in the AMANDA Back Office:**

1. Fee Description - 'TURP Permit Fee - New'
Fee amount - $320
GL Account Number - 5125 2400 9100 4087

2. Fee Description - 'TURP Permit Fee - Secondary'
Fee amount - $95
GL Account Number - 5125 2400 9100 4087

3. Fee Description - 'TURP Permit Fee - Emergency' 
Fee amount - $95
GL Account Number - 5125 2400 9100 4087

4. Fee Description - 'TURP Permit Fee - Extension'
Fee amount - $195
GL Account Number - 5125 2400 9100 4087

**Create new fee logic for the fees provided below:**
**TURP New Permit Fee**
- Applies only when work type is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.
- This fee needs to be added when a new application is created either from portal or back office
- Fee needs to be added only if folder Info 'Emergency' (#6641) and Folder Info 'Secondary' is answered 'No'. 
- Applicant must pay this fee before folder status updates to Internet Pending

**TURP Emergency Permit Fee**
- Applies only when work type is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.
- This fee needs to be added when a new application is created either from portal or back office
- Fee needs to be added only if folder Info 'Emergency' (#6641) is answered 'Yes'. 
- Applicant must pay this fee before folder status updates to Internet Pending

**TURP Secondary Permit Fee**
- Applies only when work type is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.
- Fee needs to be added only if folder Info 'Secondary' (#6321) is answered 'Yes' and Folder Info 'Emergency' is answered 'No'.
- When Folder Info 'Secondary' is answered 'Yes' and Folder Info 'Emergency' is answered 'Yes', System should insert TURP Emergency Permit Fee ONLY.  
- This fee needs to be added when a new application is created either from portal or back office
- Applicant must pay this fee before folder status updates to Internet Pending

**TURP Extension Permit Fee**
- Currently the system inserts TURP ROW fees for extensions when attempt 'Extension Granted' is made in Permit Extension Process (50680). 
- System needs to insert the TURP Permit Extension Fee at this trigger along with other fees. 
- Applies only when work type is NOT 'Franchised Utility -Gas Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Other Electric Utility', 'Franchised Utility - Telecommunication/Cable Utility'.

**Update the fee logic for the fees provided below**
**TURP ROW Usage Fees (50150) **
- This fee is currently inserted when Approved attempt is made in TURP Review Process (50520) 
- The fee logic that this fee uses is working correctly. Fee amounts for this fee has changed. Fee amounts need to be updated as per the values provided below. 
- Fee values are stored in Lookup table 50200. 
- The GL Account number for this fee is 5125 2400 9100 4062

title: Ability to override default Inspector on EX Folders
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 2-Should Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA
body:
As a reviewer on EX folders, I want process assigned users to be updated when I change the inspector name in 'Excavation Inspector' Info field. 
----
**Stakeholders: Isabelle P., Paloma A.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- System should update the assigned user for the following processes when the info field Excavation Inspector (76155) is updated 
               - Backfill (50805)
               - Concrete (Paving) (50810)
               - Concrete (Misc) (50855)
               - Pre bore (50815)
               - Consultation (50820)
               - Asphalt (Paving) (50830)
               - Plate (50835)
               - Excavation final (50860)
- The assigned user updated should correspond to the Inspector value chosen in Info field Excavation Inspector (76155). For example, if excavation inspector is chosen to be John Smith, the processes mentioned above should be assigned to the John Smith User account.  
- System should update the assigned user only if the processes mentioned above do not have a Started Date 
- System should update the assigned user only for EX folders
- Excavation Inspector Info field (76155) currently allows a user to type in a value (since it is a Pick type info field). System should look for a matching inspector user account and if found, assign the processes mentioned above to the assigned user. For example, if the user types in John Smith in Info field Excavation Inspector, system must look to see if there is a John Smith user account. If found, system should assign the processes to the John Smith user account.  

**Note:**
- Currently the info and assigned users are updated when GIS info is pulled for the folder. The implementation of this functionality should not affect the GIS pull.  


Paloma's wishlist, per #2381.
