title: EX Portal Attachments Bug (NN)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Bug Report, Impact: 3-Minor, Need: 2-Should Have, Epic, Product: AMANDA
body:
### As a EX Permit Reviewer, EX Attachments that are initially submitted by the applicant should be available on all related folders so as to not waste time looking for specific attachments in different folders. Sometimes the attachments go to non related folders.

**Stakeholders:** Kim, Paloma
**DTS Manager:** Nate

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- When the portal applicant clicks 'Submit' on an EX application, the attachments are added to the parent folder
- When the applicant clicks 'Submit' and multiple EX folder are created, the additional folders are made children of the parent folder. 
    - This will allow the users to easily find the attachment by clicking the 'View' button. 
- We need a solution/feature that informs the user, while looking at a child folder, that there are attachments available on the parent folder. 



- Reviewers will be able to access all of the files that are attached to the EX permit during the initial submittal phase, to avoid searching for the attachments on other folders other than the EX folder
- Reviewers will be able to access the attachments from the intitial submittal phase or any added after the submittal phase on any folders or child folders related to the EX Permit


----------

Description From Paloma:

> "When applicants submit for an EX they are able to select multiple streets to be impacted and AMANDA will separate that in to the necessary permits by street name.  However, it appears that AMANDA is only adding the attachments to one of those permits at random.  It’s not the biggest deal in the world but if there was a way to straighten out that kink it would be nice.
> 
> E.g., 3 or 4 files are attached that are meant to apply for the entire application. We need these files attached to all related folders. This only needs to happen upon initial submittal. The folders do not need to stay in sync after submittal. This enables permit analysts to quickly check if required documents have been provided.
> 
> Sometimes will be parent-child folders, sometimes the folders will not be connected.
> 
> CTM may flag this approach because file records will be duplicated in the AMANDA DB.
> 
> *Migrated from [atd-amanda #72](https://github.com/cityofaustin/atd-amanda/issues/72)*

Requirements:

- Attachments added during the initial submittal phase are added to the main folder instead of any child or related folders
- Attechments added during the initial submittal phase or after need to be accessible from any child or related folder

title: Inspections, Report 4
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Reports, Product: AMANDA
body:
**Stakeholder:** Ryan
Main Report Sample Layout: 
![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5f50fe1f66d1a40f7f557fb4/a60e1f1f-d317-448d-aca1-849d12d77d3c)

Acceptance Criteria: 
- From Date and To Date should be available to select as report parameters. 
- From Date and To Date is based on Folder InDate.
- Report should pull data from EX folder (all subtypes) and RW folder (Temporary Right of Way Subtype ONLY).
- Report data should not take into account any deficiencies in "Void" status 
- The data for the report needs to come from the following sources: 
-- Department: One row for each drop-down value in Info 76765
-- Number of Attempts: Sum of the number of attempts made in each qualifying folder's Traffic Control Inspection process
-- Number of Deficiencies: Sum of the number of deficiencies added in each qualifying folder's Traffic Control Inspection process 
-- Average Deficiencies: The average number of deficiencies added in each Traffic Control Inspection Process 
-- CIP: Any folder where info 76352 "CIP?" is populated as "Yes" 
-- Non-CIP: Any folder where info 76352 "CIP?" is populated as "No" 

Subreport (Drill-down) Sample layout: 

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5f50fe1f66d1a40f7f557fb4/f23d956b-ad32-4e8a-a4b7-273cd1c89ce8)

- There needs to be one table in the subreport for each department, i.e. the subreport needs to be grouped by department. 
- The data contained in the Subreport should come from the following sources:
-- Permit Number:  Folder Reference Number
-- Folder Name: Folder Name
-- CIP (Yes/No): Based on value provided in Info 76352
-- Applicant Name: Contact field of Applicant People Record in the folder
-- Right of Way Contractor: Contact field of Right of Way Contractor People Record in the folder
-- Attempt Result comment: Any attempt comments recorded in the Traffic Control Inspection Process (Each attempt comment will be one row in the drill-down report). 
-- Attempt Date: The corresponding Attempt date to each attempt comment shown in the report. 


![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cca1e522b8dfc0ee14dedf5/1697aec3-14d4-4170-9c0c-1b5ee3605d99)

title: Feature: Auto-Create Child RW-Parking for OSE
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Type: Feature, Need: 2-Should Have, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As an OSE reviewer, I'd like the system to auto-create a child parking permit folder when the folder info 'Parking Reservations' value is 'Yes'.

**Stakeholder:** Maria A
**DTS Manager:** Nate

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- This feature applies to RW-Street Event folder
- When the value of folder info 75087 'Parking Reservations' is updated to Yes, the system checks to to see if a child RW-Parking folder exists.
- If a child RW-Parking folder does not exist and the permit Analyst Accepts the "Event review" Process, the system will create the folder automatically, and create the parent/child relationship. 
- The system should copy the main property from the parent folder (not all properties need to be copied over)
- The system should copy the following from the parent to the child Parking folder: 
             - Folder Name
             - Folder Description 
             - Folder Properties
             - People Record of type 'Applicant' 
             - Folder Info "Number of days Requested"
             - Folder Info "Event Start Date"
             - Folder Info "Event End Date"
- The newly inserted RW-Parking folder should have a Folder Status of 'Pending'

title: 'Application Incomplete' AMANDA Folder Issue (TL)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Workgroup: DTS, Need: 3-Could Have, Epic, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As the system, I need to identify incomplete application folders, and update their folder status to 'Aborted', so the folders can be deleted. 
### As the folder applicant, I need to be notified in advance that my application will be removed, and given time to finish submitting it. 

**Stakeholder(s):** Paloma, Kim
**DTS Manager:** Tracy

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Once a month, they system identifies all folders with a status of 'Application Incomplete' that have not been updated in 30+ days. (Tables to check for activity: Folder, Folder Info, Folder Property)
- The system sends the folder applicant the Customer Warning email
- If, after 30 days from the customer warning email, the folder status is 'Application Incomplete', the system updates the folder status to 'Aborted'



### Customer Warning Email Template

**Subject:** Action Required - Permit Application [Folder Permit Number] 
**Body:**
Hello,

This is a message from the City of Austin about your incomplete permit application; permit details are below. Please Note: This incomplete application will be removed if it is not finished and submitted in the next 30 days.

Application Number: [Folder Number]
Application Name: [Folder Name]

To finish submitting this application follow these steps:
1. Log into the Austin Build + Connect Portal: abc.austintexas.gov 
2. Click 'My Incomplete Applications' from sidebar
3. Find this permit number; click on it
4. Click the button 'Edit and Continue' at the bottom of the page


--------

Description: Application Incomplete Issue: When a portal applicant starts an application but does not finish it, a folder for the permit is created in AMANDA with the status ‘Application Incomplete’. There are 2,757 folders in ‘Application Incomplete’ status at this time. My suggestion is to have a batch job run on the 1st of the month that will delete all Application Incomplete folders older than X amount of days.

title: Project: Open Data for ROW Permitting
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Epic, Product: AMANDA, Type: Open Data, Project Index
body:
In alignment with our value to default to open, this project aims to publish Right-of-Way permitting data to the City’s Open Data portal. This project also includes identifying a business intelligence tool for permitting managers to ingest, analyze, and report on permitting data.

## Background
This project began with a finding from the City Auditor related to traffic control inspections; we were asked to implement better methods for prioritizing and organizing the inspections being performed. These new methods depend heavily on permitting data which isn’t easily accessible in it’s current database. Permitting and inspection managers also need more access to this data, and to have the ability to perform independent queries and produce their own custom reports.

## Scope & Deliverables
The project scope includes identifying and publishing Right-of-Way permitting data on the City’s Open Data Portal. Also in scope is identifying and possibly implementing a business intelligence tool for permitting managers to work with and report on this data. 

---

title: ROWMAN6 Deliverables (Needs cleanup)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Service: Product, Epic, Project: ROWMAN Ph 6, Product: AMANDA
body:
Phase 6 of the ROWMAN Replacement Project will develop new portal features that allow Excavation and Right-of-Way permit holders to add information to permit folders that already exist in AMANDA, and are pending a customer submittal. It will also explore solutions for enabling external reviewer features that would allow our external partners to provide review comments without using AMANDA. 

## Background
The AMANDA permitting system used by ATD to manage Right of Way permitting has been upgraded recently to auto-create Excavation (EX) and Right-of-Way-Use (RW) permits when requirements for needing a permit have been met during another, related review. For example, when a Small Cell Permit (SCP) is approved the applicant is required to then apply for the EX and RW permits needed to perform the work. Currently the customer must start those online applications from scratch, which includes providing us with information we already have. With this upgrade the EX and RW permits will create themselves after the SCP is approved, and the customer will be able to pick up the already existing permits online and finish applying for them. 

In addition to auto-creating permit folders from Small Cell Permit reviews, we'd like to expand this feature to include General Permitting reviews and Utility Coordination reviews. This feature is especially valuable to Capital Improvement Project Managers; automating the creation of related Right of Way permit folders will enable to project managers to stop having to manually create each permit and delegate the permitting tasks to the CIP contractor(s). 

Some Right of Way permits include multidisciplinary reviews with internal and external stakeholders. Currently there is no feature to allow our external stakeholders to provide review comments directly to the associated AMANDA review folder. We we explore possible solutions that would enable those stakeholders to participate in the multidisciplinary reviews without needing AMANDA access. 

## Scope & Deliverables
Project Deliverables Include:
- Contractor self-assign features for EX and RW permit applications
- Automated child folder creation for UC and GP reviews
- Scoping solutions for external review features

## Desired Outcomes
Success for this project looks like:
- Auto-creation of Right of Way permits from their parent GP, UC, or SCP review.
-	Customer notification when an EX and/or RW permit requirement has been identified during another related review, with clear instructions for how to finish the application.
-	New AMANDA Portal features to allow the customer to find their pending application, provide missing details, and submit for staff review.
- A clear direction or solution for our external reviewer needs. 
 
## Timebox
The development for this project was performed in 2019 after which the project was put on hold due to re-prioritization. When this project is picked up again we will need to perform user acceptance testing, and training. Time to completion is around 3 months.

title: Product: AMANDA Case Management System
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Workgroup: ROW, Workgroup: SMB, Epic, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Product Index
body:
AMANDA is a City of Austin enterprise case management system used and managed by ATD to manage Right of Way permits, traffic control inspections, and Transportation Development Reviews. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/103247405-6792e180-492c-11eb-937f-05df16773604.png)

### Login
*Must use Internet Explorer*

AMANDA Prod: https://amandaprod.coacd.org/AMANDA5/AMANDAi.jsp 
AMANDA Test: https://amandawebtest.coacd.org/AMANDA5/AMANDAi.jsp
AMANDA Dev: https://ctmamandappdev.coacd.org/AMANDA5/AMANDAi.jsp

### Support

- You can reset your passwords [here](https://apps.austintexas.gov/eas/amanda_pw_reset/confirm_user.cfm).
- For general AMANDA support, please contact your Power User(s).
- For specific service and/or enhancement requests, Power Users should create a DTS Service request using [this form](https://atd.knack.com/dts#new-service-request/). 
- For general support that doesn't require a service request you can contact the Product Manager, Tracy Linder. 


### Background & Context

The City of Austin has been using AMANDA for over a decade now. ATD uses it primarily for all things related to development review. Our user groups include:

- ROW Management
- Transportation Development Review
- Office of Special Events

---

body:
### As Permit Reviewer, I want the folder in date to reflect the date that the folder status updated to 'Internet Pending'. 

**Stakeholders:**
Kim/Paloma

** DTS Manager:** Tracy

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- When the folder status updates to 'Internet Pending' on  RW, EX, DS, UC, PSM folders, the system inserts a new value in folder.indate. The new value = the date the status updates to 'Internet Pending'.

title: Project: ROWMAN Phase 5
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Service: Product, Epic, Project: ROWMAN Ph 5, Product: AMANDA, Project Index
body:
Phase 5 of the ROWMAN Replacement Project will deliver advanced features to the map selector tool on our online permit applications. 

## Background

ATD’s online Right of Way permit applications include a map selector tool that allows customers to use a map to identify the properties and Right of Way they wish to add to their application. This tool is capable of more features that we aren’t currently utilizing, which if used would provide greater value to customers and permit analysts. 

## Scope & Deliverables
New map selector features that we intend to develop include:
-	Copying properties from already existing applications to a new application, with the ability to edit before submitting
-	Selecting individual parking spaces, as opposed to selecting a block range and manually providing the parking meter number further in the application. 
-	Integration of existing GIS layers that will increase the applicant’s ability to self-coordinate their activity
- Integration of CIP data that will allow CIP Project Managers to import CIP data into the permit application.

## Desired Outcomes
Success for this project looks like:
-	Applicants saving time during application submittal
-	Applicants being able to identify Right-of-Way conflicts before permit submittal
-	Better parking space management across ATD
-	Increased coordination with CIP projects

## Timebox
This project is currently in the backlog, so an exact delivery date is not available at this time. We estimate that from start to completion, this project will take 3 months to deliver. 

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cca1e522b8dfc0ee14dedf5/61966d5b-2b6a-459b-84d9-0bd95db5a6f1)



---

title: Vacated ROW GIS Layer Request - E. Powers
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Data, Service: Geo, Need: 1-Must Have, Product: AMANDA
body:
**As a ROW Permit Analyst, I need to be able to see vacated ROW in ROWPACT.**


Email from Evelyn:

> Good afternoon Jamie,
> 
> My name is Evelyn Powers and I am a Project Coordinator with Right of Way Management. 
> 
> I’ve had a few discussions with Public Works and the Office of Real Estate regarding vacated streets and how Right of Way can have access to that data. We envision updating a GIS layer in one of the tools, ROWPACT, we use to reflect which streets have been vacated. ROWPACT is a GIS map which houses all kinds of information (ex: conflicting permits, jurisdiction, TCAD information, and street classification just to name a few).
> We are interested in the street layer, which shows street classification, being able to display if a street is Vacated/Private. Please see the screen shots below for how we imagine that working.
> 
> We would like you to be part of the conversation we have with your counterpart at Office of Real Estate (where the vacated street information is housed), Millicent McDonald. There seems to be some confusion as to whom would facilitate this ask. Our hope is, that by you being part of the conversation, you can bridge some of the gaps we are having, as you will “speak the same language” as them. I don’t think Office of Real Estate is quite understanding our ask since they believe the street layer would be managed by CTM. We are not asking for Office of Real Estate to make the changes, but to provide Public Works (who does manage that layer – Bryan Thompson) the GIS information they would need.
> 
> Office of Real Estate (Melissa Torres and Millicent McDonald) also mentioned that GIS has an upcoming enterprise update in the next few years and we could make the change then. Our need is a bit more urgent then that, due to Right of Way having already incorrectly permitted and charged applicants to occupy streets that have been vacated. With this new street classification being added to our arsenal, the margin for error would be significantly decreased. 
> 
> I appreciate any help or guidance you can offer on this, and if you need any clarification please let me know.

body:
### Time in ATD's Hands & Time in Applicant's Hands
**Story: I I want to be able to query by [TBD parameters] and retrieve a report that tells me, for each permit, the total time ATD staff spent actively reviewing a permit and the total time spent pending customer input/follow-up.**
- Currently the permit folders in AMANDA are not configured to capture this data; the only way to achieve this request is by upgrading all ROW permit folders to capture review cycles.
- Concern: We need to capture exactly when the customer initiates resubmittal. Currently customers provide resubmittals via email, and then we wait for ATD staff to update the permit folder with the customer response. We have to accept the resubmittals in a way that will allow the system to time-stamp the resubmittal date so we can report on it accurately. 
    - Possible solution: Implement a portal resubmittal workflow that requires the customer to resubmit as a folder attachment via portal. The attachment would then kick off the next review cycle. 
- Paloma to brainstorm w/ staff to see if there is any interim solution to this outside of the formal review process update

title: Metric: Number of review cycles
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Product: AMANDA, Project: ROW Permitting Metrics
body:
### Number of review cycles
**Story: I want to be able to query by [TBD parameters] and retrieve a report that tells me, for each permit, how many review cycles occurred.** 
- Review Cycle, in terms of permitting, is counted when a review of the activity results in a request for additional requirements from the permit applicant. The cycle begins when the review begins, and it ends when the permit analysts concludes the review by requiring additional input from the permit applicant. 
- Currently the permit folders in AMANDA are not configured to capture this data; the only way to achieve this request is by upgrading all ROW permit folders to capture review cycles.
- [ ] Paloma to brainstorm w/ staff to see if there is any interim solution to this outside of upgrading the permit folders to include a formal review process.

title: Feature: Automated DS Inspections Emails
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Feature, Workgroup: Other, Product: AMANDA
body:
### As a DS folder Right-of-Way Contractor, I want inspection information emailed to me when I pass or fail a folder inspection. 

**Stakeholders:** Michael Jones, Deborah Fonseca (DSD)
**DTS Manager:** Tracy

**NOTE:** In DSD's backlog in Service Now. **INC0086688**

### Solution:
- On DS folders, process tab
    - All inspection processes used by Mike Jones' inspectors
    - **Process names & codes need to be identified and documented**
- And for these attempt results: Pass, Fail, Failed / No Work

**Pass Attempt:**
1. The inspector (user) saves attempt 'Pass'
2. The system emails the folder people Right-of-Way Contractor 
    - Email template TBD, awaiting template from Mike
3. The system inserts the email content as a new record on the Comment tab.
    - As is doing on the BP folder when finaled. 
    - 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/109877844-1effe900-7c39-11eb-82bb-9aed21a6fa0b.png)


**Fail or Failed/No Work Attempts:**
1. The inspector inserts one or multiple process deficiencies
2. The inspector saves attempt 'Fail' or 'Failed/No Work'
3. The system emails the folder people Right-of-Way Contractor 
    - Email template TBD, awaiting template from Mike
4. The system inserts the email content as a new record on the Comment tab.
    - As is doing on the BP folder when finaled. 
    - 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/109877844-1effe900-7c39-11eb-82bb-9aed21a6fa0b.png)

**Note**
- In the scenario when multiple inspections are performed on the same permit, we would only want to send 1 email with both results. 
    - Example: Driveway Pre-pour & Sidewalk pre-pour are performed in one visit. Both inspection results should be included in one email to the Right-of-Way contractor. 
- This solution won't be effective if the Right-of-Way contractor record doesn't have an email address. This will need to be done with Paloma's staff.

title: Project: AMANDA Portal Upgrade
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Workgroup: ROW, Epic, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Project: AMANDA Portal Upgrade, Project Index
body:
We're supporting the City's upgrade of the Austin Build & Connect permitting portal, aka the AMANDA Portal. 

## Background
The [current AMANDA user portal](https://www.austintexas.gov/page/austin-build-connect-abc) is using outdated security technology that has consistently caused critical performance and security issues. It also limits our ability to develop new features. This upgrade will fix all security issues and provide us with a robust platform that will be able to grow with our business needs.

## Scope & Deliverables
The project scope is limited to duplicating all current portal features, and only includes one new feature: a permitting wizard. Currently there are two ‘Apply for Permits’ links, so we want to condense it to one.

## Timebox
This project started in October 2020, and is expected to go-live in January 2021.
-	1/4/21: Begin user acceptance testing.
-	1/11/21: Begin user training
-	1/25/21: Go-live
---

body:
Austin Build + Connect is the customer facing AMANDA platform that offers our customers online services. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/103247852-e89ea880-492d-11eb-86f5-9ebf4bbd6269.png)

### Login

https://abc.austintexas.gov/web/permit/index 

### Support

- For general AMANDA Portal support, please contact your Power User(s).
- For specific service and/or enhancement requests, Power Users should create a DTS Service request using [this form](https://atd.knack.com/dts#new-service-request/). 
- For general support that doesn't require a service request you can contact the Product Manager, Tracy Linder. 

### Background & Context

This portal provides online permitting services to the public for permits maintained in the AMANDA system. ATD customers primarily use it to apply for permits and pay fees.

title: Feature request: TIA Folder Process Cleanup(TL)
labels: Type: Feature, Need: 2-Should Have, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As a TIA reviewer, I need the folder processes to be useful. Currently none of the folder processes provide any value to us. We only need 1 process that allows us to document final TIA approval. 
_This looks ready for development._

**Stakeholders:**
Nazlie, Sangeeta

**DTS Manager:**
Tracy Linder

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- At initial folder creation, process 'Initial Intake' process is inserted
    - Process is not assigned to a user
    - 'Calculate Fees' attempt will delete any existing fees, and inserts the correct fees according to the folder info values, and updates folder status to 'Pending Payment'
    - Saving 'Calculate Fees' attempt will not close the process
    - No fees are inserted if info 'Type of Analysis' value is Subdivision or Other
    - No fees are inserted if info 'Proposed Trips Per Day' value is Other
    - 'Entered' attempt will not save if there are unpaid/unbilled folder fees
    - 'Entered' attempt when saved will close the process and insert Submittal Intake' process
- When folder fees are paid, the folder status updates to 'Paid'
-  Submittal Intake' process, on 'Complete' attempt will update folder status to 'Approved', insert folder Issue Date, and close the process.

title: Feature request: TIA Folder Status Updates (NN)
labels: Type: Feature, Need: 2-Should Have, Epic, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As a TIA reviewer, I need the folder statuses to make sense, and better align with how we are using the TIA folder. 

**Stakeholders:** Sangeeta, Nazlie
**DTS Manager:** Nate

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- At initial folder creation, fees do not insert
- At initial folder setup/creation, the status should be **Pending**
    - This is already happening (per Sree)
- After fees have been billed, the status should be **Pending Payment**
- After fees have been paid, the status should be **Paid**. This should not require user action. 
- On Submittal Intake Process, when 'Complete' attempt is saved, folder status updates to **Approved**


**Questions:**
- Are the fees the system inserts during folder insert providing value, or are they deleting them? 
- At what point in the real-life TIA workflow are fees collected? How many times are fees collected?
    - For example, many permitting processes have application fees and approval fees which are billed and paid at different times throughout the review.

title: Notify reviewer when customer uploads attachments to ABC Portal
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 3-Could Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA
body:
### As a ROW permit reviewer, I'd like the system to notify me when the customer uploads a folder attachment via the AMANDA Portal. 

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim

**Acceptance Criteria:**
Assuming user is logged in to Portal 
1. User should be able to upload attachments to portal pertaining to their applications 
2. System should be able to accept attachments based on system defined attachment types 
3. When user uploads an attachment, they system should insert a folder comment.
4. System should be able to assign the folder comment to the assignee who is handling this process. (Web application acceptance) (process code: 70,000)
5. System should  display comment at the bottom of task list for the user the comment is assigned to.

Note: comments appear under the folder and Not under the process. comments get assigned under each individual reviewer. There is also a common folder where the comments can appear which Paloma reviews. 

Questions for Paloma: What is the status of folder when waiting on attachment? Internet Pending? What is the name/type of the attachment?

=------------------ --------------
Notification when attachments are added. 

ROW routinely asks customers to add documentation to the ABC Portal. Customers constantly add documents after the initial submission. Currently ROW asks customers to notify ROW but that doesn't happen consistently. Customers end up very unhappy.

title: Feature request: TIA Folder Auto-Creation
labels: Type: Feature, Need: 3-Could Have, Workgroup: TDS, Product: AMANDA
body:
## After scoping we learned that this is not a business need and has been closed. 

### As a TIA reviewer, I'd like AMANDA to auto-create TIA folders during the site plan or zoning case review. This will allow us to stop having to enter them manually. 

**Stakeholders:** Joan M., Nazlie S, Nathan A, Sangeeta, Amber

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- TBD

**Notes for Scoping:**
- Which folders need this feature? (Zoning, Site Plan, any others?)
- What logic will the folder use to know when to create a child permit? 
- What status should the TIA folder be created in?
- What task/process will be used to assign review to TIA reviewer? 
       - Who should it assign to?
- What information, if any, will be copied from parent folders into TIA folder?
- What actions need to be done in the parent folder when a child TIA is created? (folder status change, etc.)



-----

**Describe the outcome you'd like to see when this feature is implemented.**
New TIA folders will show up on my AMANDA task list for review. 


**Describe any workarounds you currently have in place or alternative solutions you've considered.**
Currently we manually insert the folder ourselves, then we enter the info again in our TIA Primary List spreadsheet.


**What else should we know?**
This feature request came about during a requirements meeting for the TIA Module project. The requester is Joan M with the TIA group. 

**Acceptance criteria**
- TBD

title: Traffic Control Inspections Monthly Metrics Report (TL)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Reports, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
## Monthly Traffic Control Inspection Metrics Report

**Purpose:** To aid in the monthly performance metrics provided to executive management 

**Primary User:** Executive Management
[TCI Reports.xlsx](https://github.com/cityofaustin/atd-data-tech/files/4846966/TCI.Reports.xlsx)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/86034489-52caa500-ba00-11ea-86ea-465da34532bc.png)


-------------

**User Search Parameters:**
* Start Date
* End Date
* Previous Month
* Month to Date

**Query Parameters:**
* All User Parameters
* TCI Fees
* TCI Attempt Results

**Report Data (Include for each Item that meets parameters):**
* Total amount of inspection fees invoiced for the month, grouped by the inspector who created the invoice
* Total amount of inspection reports created for the month, grouped by the inspector who created the report
    * Report count = count # of attempt results on TCI process

**Misc:**
* User does not need to see details for this information, just the totals
* Consider 1st grouping to be by the inspector, then provide the totals under his/her name

title: OSE - New Processes For Neighborhood Block Party Folder (TL)
labels: Workgroup: OSE, Type: Feature, Epic, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As an Street Event Reviewer, I need to track department specific reviews for on RW, Work Type Neighborhood Block Party. Those department reviews are APD Review, Fire Review, and Trash and Recycling Review. These reviews need to populate on those department's user group tasks lists. 

**Requester:** Maria Alonzo
**DTS Manager:** Tracy
**CTM Help Desk Ticket # :** 1969325 

### Acceptance Criteria:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/97911124-666c7c00-1d10-11eb-9a45-b0ae29a6a576.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/97911146-71271100-1d10-11eb-82d5-7661924e216a.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/97911200-7e440000-1d10-11eb-802e-9319f0036e5d.png)



## Previous Acceptance Criteria:

- On folder type RW, Street Event, and work type Neighborhood (NPH), the folder will insert 3 review processes when an Approved attempt is saved on the Event Review process (50560) 
    - 72014 APD Review, 50040 Fire Review, 72008 Trash and Recycling Review.
- The "Approved" attempt should not close out the Event Review process, it should stay open
- The 3 processes should be assigned to the correct groups 
    - ACE APD, ACE ARR Review, Fire Review
- The 3 processes are grouped by 'Review' type
- Should there be a calculated end date? Yes and it should be the Event Start date
- The 3 New Review processes will automatically close (if still open) when certain attempts are saved on any of the 3 New Review processes (ACE APD, ACE ARR Review, Fire Review)
    - Attempts: Approved, Rejected, Withdrawn
- Once any of the 3 New Review Processes have an attempt of Approved, Rejected, Withdrawn; It will close out all 3 New Review Processes as well as the Event Review Process with a status of "Closed"

--------
"Event Intake" does not be inserted at all, "Event intake" Process needs to be not be inserted automatically
"Event Review" Process needs to already be there when the folder is created
The Trash and Recycling Review need to be assigned to ACE ARR Review group
The APD Review need to be assigned to ACE APD Reviewer
On the Info tab:
Add "Neighborhood Block Party" to Event type info

--------
 The "Approved" attempt should not close out the Event Review process, should stay open
Should there be a calculated end date? Yes and it should be the Event Start date
Once any of the 3 New Review Processes have an attempt of Approved, Rejected, Withdrawn; It will close out all 3 New Review Processes as well as the Event Review Process with a status of Closed

**Next Steps**
- LIT Development

[Request Details HD 1969325.pdf](https://github.com/cityofaustin/atd-amanda/files/3462946/Request.Details.HD.1969325.pdf)

title: Update DS Permit Workflow for Performance Measure Tracking(TL)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Need: 3-Could Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As a ROW Permit Manager, I need to accurately report on performance metrics on the DS folder.
**Currently, we're unable to do this because the DS folder doesn't capture when we receive the permit request, or how long it take us to perform a review.**
**- To be scoped with #1994**

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim
**DTS Manager:** Tracy

**Acceptance Criteria**
- When a DS folder is created, system should automatically insert a new process "DS Permitting Review"
- User should be able to make the following attempts on the DS Permitting Review Process: Start Review, Complete
- Attempt date should automatically be recorded when user makes an attempt in DS Permitting Review Process (this is a default AMANDA feature)
- Process status of DS Permitting Review process should be updated to Start Review when Start Review attempt is made
- Process status of DS Permitting Review process should be updated to Complete when Complete attempt is made
- System should insert the process Ended Date in DS Permitting Review process when attempt Complete is made
- DS Permitting Review Process should be mandatory for folder Issuance



Note: New Folder process to be created for DS review. List to be used “ROW INTAKE GROUP” 
 - Changes should not affect Post payment process. 


### Current Workflow
_As explained by Tracy_

1. DS permits are primarily created as part of the DSD development process, and are children of a parent BP folder
2. DS child permits, when created, default to folder status 'Pending'
3. DS customer may not initiate contact with ROW to get the permit until many months/year after the folder was created
    - For this reason, the folder In Date does not represent when the customer initiated permitting with ROW
4. When the customer initiates permitting with ROW, the permit analyst updates the folder tab, the people tab, the info tab, and the fee tab. No folder processes are used in the current workflow. 
5. When permit review is complete/approved, fees are billed and paid. 
6. The permit is issued after payment of fees
7. Due to this workflow, ROW is unable to answer these questions:
    - When did the customer initiate permitting with ROW?
    - How long did it take ROW to perform the DS review?


------

Description: Currently the DS folder is not configured to capture when the PLA receives a request to process the permit, so performance measure tracking is not possible.

title: Bug: TCI Inspection Attempt Type 'Return To Work' (TL)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Epic, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As the system, when a 'Return to Work' attempt is saved on  50685 Traffic Control Inspection, I need to update the folder status to be whatever was in place when the 'Project Suspension' attempt was saved. 

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Ryan M., Kim
**DTS Manager:** Tracy Linder

**Further Info:**
- 'Return to Work' is only used by staff when 'Project Suspension' has previously been saved
- When 'Project Suspension' attempt is saved, the folder could be in any valid status
- When 'Project Suspension' attempt is saved, the folder status updates to 'Suspended'
- When 'Return to Work' is saved, staff expects the folder status to update to whatever folder status was in place when the 'Project Suspension' attempt was saved
    - Currently the system updates folder status to 'Active', which creates issues for staff, and customers. This is problematic for any scenario in which the folder was not 'Active' when the Project Suspension took place. 

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- 'Return to Work' attempt on 50685 Traffic Control Inspection will not save if 'Project Suspension' attempt does not already exist.
- Saving the 'Return to Work' attempt will update the folder status back to what is was when 'Project Suspension' was saved
    - Exception: The folder status should not update to 'Active' if the folder expiration date is in the past. Instead, it should update to 'Expired.
- These features work on the following folder types: DS, EX, RW, ECV
- These features work not just once, but as many times as needed on the same process


![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cca1e522b8dfc0ee14dedf5/2e334d87-635f-4a8a-ac72-578bfee679ec)

ROW has been directed to gather data related to our CIP case load.  I believe step one to this will be a custom report.

body:
### As a ROW permit applicant, I'd like to be able to figure out if my project is in City of Austin jurisdiction before applying. I'd like a tool available on the splash page to help me. 

**Stakeholders:** Paloma
**DTS Manager:** TBD

**Acceptance Criteria**
- Add to the AB&C portal, Apply for ROW Permits page: 
    - **Note:** Right of Way Management only issues permits for City of Austin Full Purpose Jurisdiction (COA FPJ).  Before submitting your request, check [here](https://www.austintexas.gov/gis/JurisdictionsWebMap/ ) to determine the jurisdiction.  Application fees are not refundable for requests that fall outside of the COA FPJ.


![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cca1e522b8dfc0ee14dedf5/599f75ee-725d-4d77-bb07-882dc4dfb7ec)


<!-- Email -->
<!-- paloma.amayo-ryan@austintexas.gov -->

> What application are you using?

Other / Not Sure
AMANDA v6 Portal: Austin Build + Connect (see attachment)

> Describe the problem.

I'd like to add some language to the Apply for Right of Way Permits / Special Events initial/splash page.

Include the following as a second paragraph:
"Right of Way Management only issues permits for City of Austin Full Purpose Jurisdiction (COA FPJ).  Before submitting your request, check here to determine the jurisdiction.  Application fees are not refundable for requests that fall outside of the COA FPJ."

The customer would be linked to the City's jurisdiction map - https://www.austintexas.gov/gis/JurisdictionsWebMap/ 



> Describe the outcome you'd like to see when this feature is implemented.

This will help our ROW customers from needlessly applying for (and paying for) a permit which we don't review.

> Describe any workarounds you currently have in place or alternative solutions you've considered.

Currently we refund customers who errantly submit applications outside of the FTJ.  This is counter ordinance which states that application fees are non-refundable.  We've considered not issuing refunds to these customers, since our main permit webpage already addresses this, but this hasn't gone over well with customers.

> Is there anything else we should know?

No specific date but as we push more customers online the need becomes more pressing.  Hopefully this is a quick/easy fix though!

body:
**Status as of May 26: ATD testing found no issues to report. Stakeholders have been updated. Next DSD & Finance need to test their portion of this fix.**

### Overview:
- Dec 2018: SCP Phase 2 went live
    **- Included in this release was an update to SCP fees, instructing the system to calculate the % of fee breakdown to each FDU**
- March 2019: DSD reported a bug with their FDU report caused by the update to SCP fees 
- Spring 2019: Controller's Office reported a massive backlog of AMANDA fees collected that were unable to be deposited due to the SCP fee bug(s). 
    **- Basically the way the SCP fees were configured makes it impossible for the related FDU code to populate on any of the reports that finance staff & other finance systems depend on.** 
- 6/13/19: All SCP stakeholder departments met @ Barton Oaks to discuss this issue & solutions
    - An interim solution was implemented; DSD agreed to manually populate FDU codes for the controller's office. This will allow the money to be deposited while the fee fixes were being developed. 
- Summer 2019: CTM engaged Unisys to perform the development needed 
- 8/5/19 - George w/ CTM promoted Unisys' dev to TEST
- Late Aug 2019 - DSD & ATD provided UAT feedback
- 11/8/19 - Tracy L, Deanna D, & Mark C synced on the project & identified next steps
    - CTM committed to performing the necessary development to get this to PROD
- Dec 2019 - George performed development & promoted to TEST
- Pending UAT from ATD & DSD

title: SCP Transport Facility Fee Programming (TL)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Workgroup: Other, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA
body:
### As an SCP case manager reviewing the Transport Facility subtype, I do not need to collect/review information about each individual street segment. 

### As an SCP case manager reviewing the Transport Facility subtype, I need to know how many total network nodes the Transport Fiber is feeding, as a folder info. 

### As an SCP Transport Facility applicant, I need to pay the correct application and approval fee amounts, based on total network nodes. 

**Stakeholder:** April Sellars
**DTS Manager:** Tracy

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- These updates only apply to the Transport Facility subtype of the SCP folder
- The portal application no longer asks the customer to provide any data for the Network Nodes/Attachments free form tab (see image below, the section that is crossed out). 
- A new folder info is created, Info Description: # of Network Nodes Fed by Transport Facility
- The new info populates on the portal application for the customer to fill out. It is a mandatory field, and the portal description is 'How man network nodes is the Transport Fiber feeding?' 
- When the portal applicant clicks 'Submit' the correct application fee is inserted & billed
- The application fee logic is as follows:
    - Fee calculates based on the value of the new info '# of Network Nodes Fed by Transport Facility'.  A $500 flat fee is charged for nodes 1-5. For each pole over 5, $250 is charged.
    -  If value is 1-5, the fee is $500 
    - If value is greater than 5, $500 + $250 for each value over 5 is charged
    - Example 1: Value = 6, Application Fee = $750
    - Example 2: Value = 4, Application Fee = $500
    - Example 3: Value = 8, Application Fee = $1,250
- When the system bills the SCP Approval Fees, the logic is updated as follows: 
    - A prorated ROW usage fee is calculated for the remaining months in the year. Fee logic is $20.83 * Total # of Nodes/Poles * # of full months left in the calendar year. The Total # of Nodes/Poles value is retrieved from the new folder info. 
    - An annual ROW usage fee is calculated. Fee logic is $250 * Total # of Nodes/Poles * Years Paid For. The Total # of Nodes/Poles value is retrieved from the new folder info. Years Paid For is retrieved from folder info 76116
    - The prorated fee and the annual fee are added together, and inserted as a total amount. 

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cca1e522b8dfc0ee14dedf5/034efbd0-3571-4a1b-a19d-56eba65ba1d7)

title: AOB Review - Data Cleanup for Contractor Pick List
labels: Type: Meeting, Workgroup: ROW, Service: Product, Product: AMANDA
body:
### 8/13/20 AOB Meeting

**People record type ‘City Owner’ Info:**
-	ATD uses this people type as a solution/workaround for entities that are performing ROW work, but do not require a ROW license because they’re COA or a franchise. 
-	Currently there are 433 ‘City Department’ people records. Only a small fraction of those represent entities that do not require a ROW license.
-	This causes the ROW portal applications to display hundreds of inaccurate ‘valid contractors’ for applicants to select from
-	This may also lead to ROW issuing a permit without a valid contractor listed. 
-	Our goal is to only populate valid contractor records for the portal applicants
**Questions for AOB:**
-	Is anyone using ‘City Department’ for a specific business need?
-	If we cleaned up ‘City Department’ records to only those that ROW needs, would that have negative impacts?
-	If cleaning up the ‘City Department’ records is not an ideal solution, we’ll need to create a new people type. Any objections?

title: BUG UC/LM Self Assign: Aborting Process
labels: Type: Bug Report, Project: ROWMAN Ph 3, Product: AMANDA
body:
### As a UC applicant who is attempting to self-assign, I need the ability to stop the process and come back at another time to finish.

**UAT Results:**
When I was in the middle of the self-assign process on portal, the system froze up, so I closed it out and attempted to start over, however portal told me that 'this permit is not available for self-assign'. I had to go to backoffice and update the folder status from 'Application Pending' to 'Pending Customer Action', and then I was able to try again. 

**Acceptance Criteria**
- The system allows customers to start the self-assignment process, leave the portal before finishing, and come back at a later time to finish. 
- This story applies to the LM folder also

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cca1e522b8dfc0ee14dedf5/f5fe48c3-c1c5-41a9-9236-163554b17221)

title: Bug, Self-Assign: Buttons Causing Negative Results
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Bug Report, Project: ROWMAN Ph 3, Product: AMANDA
body:
**On the Info page, pressing the 'Search Again' button does the following:**
- Takes user back to Assign Permits
- Updates the folder status to 'Application Pending'
    - This essentially makes it impossible for any customer to pick this application up and finish it

**On the attachments page, pressing the 'Cancel this application' button does the following:**
- Takes user back to Assign Permits
- Updates the folder status to 'Aborted'
    - This essentially makes it impossible for any customer to pick this application up and finish it
    - Also, this folder will end up being deleted by the system if this isn't caught in time by staff/customers

### Questions for Unisys re: Solutions:
- Info Page: Remove 'Search Again' as an option
- Attachments page: Remove 'Cancel this Application' as an option
- See #2950 - add the button that makes saving & continue later an option
- Give the customer the ability to abort everything they've done, and update the folder so that another customer (or the same one) can come back at another time to self-assign. 


------

title: Film Permit Expiration Date Issue (TL)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Bug Report, Need: 1-Must Have, Epic, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### As the system, I need to expire RW-Film permits at 3:00am the day after the folder expiration date.
### As they system, I need to set the RW-Film permit expiration date to the last date of permit approval.

**DTS Manager:**
Tracy Linder

**Stakeholders:**
Kim, Paloma, Evelyn Powers

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Upon folder issuance, the RW-Film folder inserts a value in the folder expiration date that follows this logic:
    - (Value in folder info 75605 'Start Date') + (value in folder info 75640 Total Number of Days) -1 = Expiration Date
    - Day 1 of permit approval is the start date, that's why we subtract 1 from Start Date + Total # of Days
    - Example: (Test Folder RSN 12317823) Start Date info is 9/16/19. Total # of Days info is 3. So the folder expiration date should be 9/18/19.
- The RW-Film folder status updates to expired at 3:00 am the day after folder expiration
    - Following the above example, the folder should expire at 3:00 am on 9/19/19


---


Description: The film permit expiration calculation is odd and not always consistent. Evelyn should be able to explain more.

title: UAT: UC/LM Self-Assignment, Round 2
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Testing, Project: ROWMAN Ph 3, Product: AMANDA
body:
**UAT Feedback Needed From:**

- [x] CPO (Greg Pepper)
- [x] UC Team (Jaclyn, Isaiah)
- [ ] LM Team (Andy, Melissa)


Hi Team,

The testing instructions I promised you are below. Hopefully everyone can still meet the testing deadline of this Friday. Please text or call my cell if you need any help. 

Thanks Everyone!
Tracy


**Testing Instructions** 
 
1.	Log into AMANDA TEST & Portal Test
a.	Reset password here if needed 
2.	In AMANDA Test, locate an SP folder to test on
a.	Folder Status shouldn't matter, but In Review is easier to work with
b.	Make sure the folder doesn't already have child UC/LM folders
3.	On the People Tab of the SP, make yourself the applicant
a.	Replace the current applicant with your test people record. Ask for help with this if needed. 
4.	On the Info Tab of the SP, update the UC or LM review info to 'YES' & press Save
a.	 
5.	Verify that a child folder was created 
a.	If no child folder was created, testing cannot continue; contact Tracy
6.	Verify the status of the new folder is 'Pending Customer Action'
7.	Verify that you received an email (as the applicant of the SP folder)
a.	Does the email say what you want it to say? Do  you have email feedback? 
b.	If you didn’t receive an email, check to see if you followed step #3
8.	Open the child UC or LM folder; you will need the permit number & folder ROW ID to continue
9.	In Test Portal, click 'Assign Permit'
10.	Follow the on-screen directions to enter the permit & pin #
a.	The pin # is the Folder ROW ID
11.	Submit a test application
12.	In AMANDA, open or refresh the folder that you just submitted an application for
a.	Status should be Internet Pending 
b.	Everything else about the folder should match what you expect an internet pending folder to look and behave like

title: Out-of-System Fees (Audit Request)
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
## Out-of-System Fees
_AKA # 49 Out of Process TCP Fees, # 211 New GF Subtype, ROW's #1 Priority, Outstanding Audit Request_

**Note:** We discovered that both these issues are part of the same user story.
    - #211 will be closed 

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim, Mooney

**User Story:** As the ATD Cashier at Toomey, I need to record all fees i accept in one system of record. The few remaining fees not in AMANDA should be added ASAP. 

**User Story:** As the person paying an 'out of process' fee, I need to be able to pay those fees online.

**Future State:**
_When ROW staff need to collect an 'out of process' fee_
1. In AMANDA, create a new GF folder, choose subtype ATD
2. Add the project location (site address) to the folder property tab
3. Add people record types Applicant, and Billed-To to the people tab
4. **Need SME Input** Complete required info fields on the info tab
    - Kim was unsure if TCP Review staff will want any info tab fields. Perhaps the TCP #? 
5. Insert & bill the fee(s), provide customer with the invoice
    - The folder status will be 'Pending Payment'
6. The customer pays the fee
7. The folder status updates to 'Payment Complete' -End Process-

- Brandi is best to ask for a list of fees collected outside of AMANDA
- The General Fees (GF) folder in AMANDA is what other departments are using to record fees outside of a specific case folder
- TCP Review Fee is being collected manually
    - **Need SME Input**
    - Amount? Flat Fee - no logic
    - Name of Fee?
    - ATD Surcharge?
---------

Old Description: ROW Fee audit recommendation that out of process TCP review fees be captured in AMANDA ASAP. 
Two Options TBD:
1. Create new fee and apply it on existing folder types
2. Create new (very simple) folder and fee

title: Meeting to Discuss Changes made to #1518 Unpaid Fee Flag on Permit Issuance
labels: Type: Meeting, Workgroup: ROW, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
### Meeting to Discuss Findings from #1518 Unpaid Fee Flag on Permit Issuance
-----

**Meeting Date/Time:**  June 4, 2020 @ 130-2pm
**Attendees:** Nate, Tracy, Sree, Paloma, Kim

- A demo from Sree on 6/3 showed us that if there any unpaid ATD fees for the people ID used, AMANDA would throw a Warning upon issuance of Folder. Once the message is "OK'd", the permit is issued and goes Active.
    - The Issue we found with this is that the permit should not be issued or go Active if there are unpaid fees once the Warning is accepted.
    - This also raised the concern of the giving the Reviewer the option to issue the permit if it is a special situation or case.
- The verbiage on the error was changed to say total amount of fee owed and people id. Does not say what folder or fee (Reviewer will have to Research).

### Solutions Identified for Stakeholder Consideration:
- Change process to a folder Process attempt (This is a good one but will it hinder workflow or add value?)
- Set monetary limit for hard stop (permit not issued) and any fees less have warning (Permit is issued)
- Hard stop (Permit not issued)
- Warning only (Permit is issued)

**Challenges:** 
- Reviewer needs the option to issue or not issue the permit if there are any unpaid ATD fees
- Current Permit issuance process does not check to see if the process has already been done for that particular permit/PeopleID in order to NOT issue the permit and allow the Reviewer to see what unpaid fees there are. 
- Cannot make changes to Main Folder Page error (allows for more options in the warning) due to it being a web page code configuration change that would involve CTM.

**Next Steps:**

- [x] Create Meeting w/Kim and Paloma

- [ ] Get feed back on which option they would prefer going with

- [ ] Get LIT Estimate of work/complexity from changes (possible time frame)

title: PNTS Active Transportation System Issues
labels: Workgroup: ATSD, Type: Bug Report, Impact: 2-Major, Epic, Product: AMANDA
body:
### The problem, as described by customer Dylan J.:

I wanted to elevate this issue to you as we’ve been experiencing PNTS Geoloader errors ongoing for the past number of weeks, which has made it difficult to plan often time-sensitive communications work around. I and others have submitted tickets to CTM and emailed Prentice Mooney (e.g., tickets for Parkfield, Cherrywood, 46th-47th and I know of Webberville, one of the Shoal Creek construction notices, Healthy Streets). 
 
Prentice seems to think that it may be maintenance to the AMANDA system, scheduled or unscheduled, that prevents AMANDA from creating corresponding folders for the PNTS using the GeoLoader. Sometimes it resolves itself in a day or two, but you have to check back repeatedly. The workaround for smaller address pulls is to do it manually using Google maps, but this doesn’t work for larger projects. 
 
Would it be possible to reach out to whoever manages the AMANDA system and see if there’s another solution than just hoping it’ll work when you need it to? It might be helpful to better understand the system’s maintenance schedule, or if there’s a solution to keep the GeoLoader from breaking so often that someone is working on. 
 
Thanks for your help with this,
 
Dylan J.

------

### Resolution:

No helpful resolution can be identified at this time. Prentice with CTM-GIS thinks this issue is caused by attempting to run PNTS while AMANDA is down for maintenance, but I'm not convinced that is the true cause. She's added all PNTS users to the AMANDA user distribution list, so they can plan around scheduled maintenance. **I've asked users to send me an email each time they encounter this error,** so I can compile a log that will allow us to find the related system error logs and hopefully get to the bottom of the error. We can also use it to compare to AMANDA system maintenance and determine if that is truly the issue. 
- Tracy

title: Feature: Unpaid Fee Flag on Permit Issuance
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA, Provider: LaunchIT
body:
## This issue on hold until AMANDA V7 Implementation 

## Unpaid Fee Flag
_AKA # 46 Unpaid Fee Flag on Permit Issuance (Audit Request)_

**Stakeholders:** Paloma, Kim, Mooney

**User Story:** As a ROW permit analyst (PLA), I need to know if any of the folder people have unpaid ROW fees BEFORE the permit is issued, so I can place the permit on hold and attempt to collect the outstanding fee(s).

**Current State:**
1. The PLA, prior to permit approval, performs manual research to identify any unpaid ROW fees for ALL people listed on the people tab (Contractor, applicant, contact, whoever). 
    - They do not collect fees billed before 10/1/2013.
2. If no outstanding fees are identified, the permit is issued. End process. 
3. If outstanding ATD fees are identified, the PLA provides the outstanding fee information to the person/entity responsible for payment. 
    - So if there are 3 unique people/entities on the permit, each entity will be provided with their unique fee information. 
    - The people/entities are provided with instructions for paying, all outstanding bill numbers, and the total for each bill number. 
4. The PLA adds a note to the folder description: "Pending Outstanding Fee Payment **TL"
5. The customer will pay the fees, either online or in person. 
6. The customer notifies PLA of payment
    - When this step is missed, it leads to customers working in the ROW without an approved permit
7. PLA issues the permit. End Process. 

**Future State:**
1. Folder issuance is attempted, either by a user from the folder tab, or by a system procedure like post payment.
    - We need to be sure any new procedure doesn't cause payment update failures when the fees are paid online. (Put simply, lets learn from the issues caused by the Post Payment upgrade.)
    - This feature may have to be split into 2 features, one for running this procedure when issuance is initiated by the user from the folder tab, and another for running this procedure when issuance is initiated by a post payment procedure. **Will need LIT feedback on this.**
2. The system performs the unpaid fee verification
    - See # 1 in Current State; the system needs to do this instead of the PLA
    - Query all unpaid fees for each people record on the people tab. Of those fees, exclude any not in folder types RW, EX, LC, ECV, GF, or DS. Of those fees, exclude any created prior to 10/1/2013. **Now you have a list of qualifying fees.** 
3. If **qualifying fees** are found, an alert window opens informing the PLA that unpaid fees were found. 
    - The window will display this text: A people record related to this permit has unpaid ROW fees!
        - **Stakeholder input needed.** Please provide feedback on the proposed content of the alert window:    
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/74903386-60935e00-536e-11ea-9440-7aa50dc414c4.png)
    - The window will facilitate the following actions:
        - Allow the user to click a button to continue with permit issuance
        - Allow the user to click a button to abort the permit issuance, and view information related to the qualifying fees
        - The people invoice list view is an example of how we might provide the user with data about the qualifying fees:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49930868/74903558-e0212d00-536e-11ea-968f-a603023fc067.png)
4. PLA will provide the unpaid fee information (see list view above) to the customer, and note 'Pending Outstanding Fee Payment**' in the folder description.
    - If it's possible to email the 'list view' of unpaid fees to the customer from the window in AMANDA, that would be ideal **Will need LIT feedback on this.**
5. Customer pays
    - Jump to # 8 if customer does not pay
6. AMANDA notifies the PLA (or perhaps a resource task list?) that the permit needs to be issued **Stakeholder input needed. How would they most like to be notified?**
7. PLA issues the permit. End Process.
8. **Stakeholder input needed.** Will ROW need/want to know that these fees are still unpaid after a certain amount of time? For example, a monthly report emailed by the system with info about all 'fee flag alerts' that occurred in the previous month; only include info for fees that are still unpaid.
    - This would be another story/feature however LIT needs to be aware of the reporting requirement when developing the fee flag feature. 
------

title: Custom Report: TCI Violation Fees
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Need: 1-Must Have, Type: Reports, Type: Enhancement, Product: AMANDA
body:
**This was put in the Ice Box on 6/29/20, after a conversation w/ Ryan M. Investigation fee processes are under legal review; best to wait until that's worked out before working on this issue.**

-------

### Email From Ryan Ward 9/18/19:

Tracy,

I would like to request a daily report that captures Violation Fees. We’re working on process improvements to add Quality Control (QC), as to how we fee the customer. There have been some fees contested recently and we review each one of those instances. This list would give us the ability to see what fees were assessed each day, so we can review validity. Just another transparency effort on our part.

Let me know if this is something you can generate or if it will have to be a project. Also, what the timeframe would be for completion.

On another note, could you run a report that shows each inspector, with relation to the fees they have assessed, broken down monthly for this FY?

Thanks,
Ryan

---
## Report #1 - Daily Fee Report
**Purpose:** Allow the supervisor to perform an accountability review on all inspection fees billed on any given day.

**Primary User:** Inspection Supervisor (Mani)

**User Search Parameters:**
* Start Date 
* End Date

**Query Parameters:**
* TCI Inspection Fees
* Start Date
* End Date

**Report Data (Include for each Item that meets parameters):**
* The inspection fee
* Link to open the permit folder, directly to the fee tab if possible
* Fee info (name, amount, date billed, payment status, bill #, invoiced by user ID)
* Folder #
* Contractor info

**Misc:**
* Group the report data by the permit #
* A daily batch report would be nice, not necessary
----

**Issue #149 was opened for the 2nd report request related to metrics.**

title: AMANDA Product Challenge: UAT Stakeholder Resources
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Service: Product, Epic, Product: AMANDA
body:
## AMANDA development resources became available to DTS in April 2020, however no issues have moved to the Closed pipeline to date. 

**Although we should consider the ramp up time that new resources take, it is alarming that no issues have been completed. Luckily however, we've identified this issue early enough to implement proactive solutions.** 

**Probable Cause:** AMANDA DTS issues are getting stuck at Review/QA and Ready to Deploy.
- 4 Issues in Review/QA
- 2 Issues in Ready to Deploy

**Other Indications that UAT is the Block:**
- Stakeholders expressing wanting very much to provide feedback, but just not having time to finish
- Poor results when attempting to elicit feedback by email
- Better, good results when attempting to elicit feedback by scheduling Teams meetings

**Proposed Solutions:**
- Schedule a reoccurring weekly meeting with this group of stakeholders to gather feedback and to facilitate testing. 
- Educate stakeholders on our approach to development, especially our sprint cadences, and what to expect
- After each sprint planning session, email stakeholders with the sprint goals, and together measure if the stakeholders have the resources for each item in the sprint. 
- Create a standard process for DTS AMANDA to follow when an issue is pending customer feedback
    - Add **Status: Pending stakeholder response** to the top of the issue description (Tracy not a big fan; too much overhead)
- Ask ROW to designate a SPOC from their group of power users (PU).
    - It's difficult for us to know which PU should be contacted for any given issue, resulting in having to include all of them on emails, which in turn creates some unnecessary email clutter. 
    - The thought is we can email the SPOC, who can forward it to the correct power user. 
- Tracy and Nate to learn more about what each PU does, and how they contribute as a PU. 
- To help improve the efficiency of email communications, Tracy will introduce email standards to the stakeholder team.
    - Subject Line should begin with the DTS ticket number & name (or shortened name, be flexible)
    - Tracy or Nate will add a link to the github issue when sending the first email in a thread, or responding for the first time in a thread
    - Only discuss 1 DTS ticket per email (unless it makes more sense to discuss multiple, related tickets. Be flexible!) 
- Use a new label like 'Awaiting Response' to better identify issues that may be delayed due to this issue, and will need more followup than we may have considered. 
    - Per team feedback, we'll try using the Blocked pipeline to meet this need, and circle back if it doesn't help. 
    - If we do end up using a label, be sure to use a Status: type. 
- Schedule bi-weekly check-ins on this issue to determine if these solutions work. We'll know we've solved this issue when we start seeing issues consistently update to Closed.

### Bug: User needs to be able to re-assign the Assigned User on 51411 - AW Pipeline Engineering. Currently the system will not allow this. 
-----

**Reported By:** Greg P.
**User:** Eric S.
**Service Now:** CALL0036081
<!-- Eric Sermeno -->


<!-- Email -->
<!-- greg.pepper@austintexas.gov -->

> What application are you using?

Other / Not Sure

> Describe the problem.

In the Utility Coordination (UC )Folder in AMANDA, Austin Water has requested a new SOP for Austin Water utility (AW) Reviews within the UC folder to meet a critical business need for them, ATD, CPO, and for applicants such as PWD, Watershed, and other Depts. 
The new AW SOP requires that;
1. AW Infrastructure Management Reviewer 51374 reviews first 2 submittals
2.  If Rejected by a reviewer within the AW- Infrastructure Group, that reviewer will also reject the AW Pipeline Engineering Review  51364.
3. Once AW Pipeline Reviewer Approves that folder, that reviewer will Approve both disciplines. 
Request:  Please allow permission within the UC Folder to allow for any of the AW Infrastructure Management Reviewers lookup table to attempt the process within the
AW Pipeline Engineering process 51363 and vice versa. 
On the UC Folder, both sets of reviewers should be able to complete processes for the other. 
Please note that we will be utilizing the "AW-Pipeline Engineering" Group Account within the reviewer lookup table 51374 until an individual within that group is assigned. 

> How soon do you need this?

Soon — This week 

> Is there anything else we should know?

The Corridor Program Office has critical work that required this new AW process to be in place to complete our reviews in a timely manner. ATD-CPO has 2016 Mobility Bond plans and waivers in the AW Review queue that are being held until we can get these requests into the AMANDA UC Folder. The new AW process will delay these critical safety projects if we cannot get these permissions up and running quickly. 
As the owner of the UC folder, creator of the UC processes, and the AULCC Chairman, no other permissions should be required to complete this request FOR THIS FOLDER ONLY! I am working directly with AW for this request. If this changes anything within the enterprise-wide folder processes, please let me know ASAP. 
Thanks for the help!!

Requested By
> Greg P.

title: EX Folder Fee Bug
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Bug Report, Impact: 2-Major, Product: AMANDA
body:
### EX child folder status is updating to 'Application Incomplete' when the customer presses submit online. 
**Stakeholder:** Kimberly P. w/ ROW, copy Paloma
**Service Now:** CALL0036082

The EX folder portal application is programmed, when pressing the submit button, to create a folder for each street added to the application. After the customer presses submit, all folders created as part of this workflow should immediately update folder status to 'Pending Payment'. **This is currently not happening anymore.** Instead, only the parent folder updates to 'Pending Payment', and all child folders update to 'Application Incomplete'. 

The system is currently allowing the customer to pay fees on the child folders that are 'Application Incomplete', and when that happens, the folder status does not update, and as such, never lands in queue for staff review. **This is a major issue.** 

Finally, the system is also allowing the customer to continue applying for the child folders with 'Application Incomplete' status, and upon submittal, inserts & bills the same fees that have already been inserted & billed, thereby double charging the applicant and causing staff to have to perform refunds. **Also a major issue.**

**Solution:** Update the code so the child folders of this process update to 'Pending Payment' after submitting. 

------

AMANDA

title: Test Possible Issue: Post Payment
labels: Workgroup: ROW, Type: Bug Report, Type: Testing, Project: ROWMAN Ph 3, Product: AMANDA
body:
Per Kim, when an activation fees are billed separately, and only one is paid, the folder will auto-issue and it shouldn't. 

Story: PLA bills for activation fees, but they are not paid. Then something changes, more activation fees or investigation fees are added. If only one of these bills are paid, the permit will issue itself.

title: Email Template - LM Self Assignment
labels: Service: Product, Workgroup: Other, Project: ROWMAN Ph 3, Product: AMANDA, Provider: Unisys
body:
### As a Site Plan applicant, I need to be notified when a child LM folder is created for self-assignment, and given information about next steps.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- When the LM child folder is created as part of the self-assign workflow,

**Template:**
- **Subject Line:** [SP Folder Name] - Land Management Application Required

You are receiving this email because your Site Plan for [SP permit number] requires you to submit a Land Management (LM) application. Please note that an LM case file has been created and is now attached to your site plan application. 

Your LM case file ID number (ROWID/FolderRSN) is [folderRSN]. All correspondence with our office should include your LM case file number. 

Next Step: Please contact the Office of Real Estate Services to set up a meeting with one of our Property Agents, who will direct you in submitting an application and next steps. Contact us by phone at 512-974-7090. 

Thank You,
Office of Real Estate Services

body:

**Resolution: Users who add attachments that need to be viewable on portal should be sure to select 'AMANDA Images' as the attachment type.** 

---
**Customer:** Greg P.


<!-- Email -->
<!-- greg.pepper@austintexas.gov -->

> What application are you using?

AMANDA

> Describe the problem.

The AMANDA UC Folder attachments are not visible to the AMANDA Applicant / Internet user through the AB+C Portal/ROWMAN portal. All attachments on that folder should be visible to all people on the People Tab. However, the first step, and most critical step, is to allow the Applicant to see the attachments, including attachments uploaded by the reviewers on the folder such as Austin Water. This is a critical function of the folder and the newly instituted Blue Beam review (Electronic Plan review)  

> Is there anything else we should know?

WIth the Work From Home orders, this is a critical function missing from the UC Folder.
Applicants are not able to complete coordination without this function and ability to see comments made from City Reviewers. This could affect public safety and utility systems.

> Website Address

ROWMAN &  https://abc.austintexas.gov/f

Internet Browser: Chrome

Requested By
> Greg P.
